WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:26.728 --> 00:00:30.264
<i>Hear now the song of Troy.</i>

3
00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:34.268
<i>and of the years</i>
<i>the sea would not forget.</i>

4
00:00:34.334 --> 00:00:35.637
<i>There was a city once...</i>

5
00:00:35.703 --> 00:00:37.170
<i>Land ahoy!</i>

6
00:00:37.237 --> 00:00:39.807
<i>Walls higher than</i>
<i>any siege tower.</i>

7
00:00:39.874 --> 00:00:43.645
<i>thick enough that no</i>
<i>battering ram could crack them.</i>

8
00:00:43.711 --> 00:00:46.981
<i>A city that should</i>
<i>never have fallen.</i>

9
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:49.149
<i>crowned in gold.</i>

10
00:00:49.216 --> 00:00:52.787
<i>its walls raised</i>
<i>by the hands of gods.</i>

11
00:00:52.854 --> 00:00:57.391
<i>Prince of Troy. Paris.</i>
<i>set his heart on Helen.</i>

12
00:00:57.457 --> 00:01:00.327
<i>wife of Menelaus.</i>
<i>king of Sparta.</i>

13
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:02.764
<i>a woman already claimed.</i>

14
00:01:02.830 --> 00:01:06.366
<i>He carried her away</i>
<i>to have her as his own.</i>

15
00:01:07.669 --> 00:01:11.673
<i>And so the kingdoms of</i>
<i>Greece rose as one.</i>

16
00:01:11.739 --> 00:01:16.511
<i>For ten long years Greece</i>
<i>laid siege to Troy.</i>

17
00:01:16.578 --> 00:01:20.347
<i>Spears broke. but</i>
<i>their walls did not.</i>

18
00:01:20.414 --> 00:01:23.051
<i>Among the Greeks</i>
<i>walked a man who carried</i>

19
00:01:23.116 --> 00:01:25.553
<i>no sword sharper than his mind.</i>

20
00:01:25.620 --> 00:01:28.322
<i>He knew what the</i>
<i>others could not see:</i>

21
00:01:28.388 --> 00:01:31.091
<i>that Troy would not be broken.</i>

22
00:01:31.158 --> 00:01:33.595
<i>It would have to be deceived.</i>

23
00:01:39.067 --> 00:01:42.704
<i>Odysseus. king of Ithaca.</i>

24
00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:47.775
<i>patient as the tide.</i>
<i>cunning as a fox in winter.</i>

25
00:01:51.244 --> 00:01:53.681
<i>A decades long war had ended.</i>

26
00:01:53.748 --> 00:01:57.284
<i>but for Odysseus.</i>
<i>the longest journey</i>

27
00:01:57.351 --> 00:01:58.720
<i>was only just beginning.</i>

28
00:01:59.887 --> 00:02:01.556
The King!

29
00:02:01.623 --> 00:02:03.091
King Odysseus!

30
00:02:03.156 --> 00:02:06.126
Our men are gone.
but Troy is fallen.

31
00:02:06.193 --> 00:02:07.795
and our battle is won.

32
00:02:07.862 --> 00:02:09.262
Where are we going?

33
00:02:09.329 --> 00:02:11.231
Home.
To my kingdom.

34
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:13.801
To my son. My wife.

35
00:02:13.868 --> 00:02:15.036
You may join me.

36
00:02:15.103 --> 00:02:16.671
Be an advisor
in my court.

37
00:02:16.738 --> 00:02:21.943
For your bravery in this
terrible war. I will ensure

38
00:02:22.010 --> 00:02:24.779
you will want for nothing
for the rest of your life.

39
00:02:24.846 --> 00:02:27.214
Thank you. my King.

40
00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:29.416
It would be my honor.

41
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:31.919
The journey will not be easy.

42
00:02:31.986 --> 00:02:35.823
I will swim if I must.
but I will get home.

43
00:02:39.159 --> 00:02:40.293
Trojans!

44
00:02:42.096 --> 00:02:43.430
If the gods are willing.

45
00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:16.496
Tell me. O Muse.
the man of many devices.

46
00:03:16.564 --> 00:03:19.667
who wandered full
many ways after he had

47
00:03:19.734 --> 00:03:23.336
sacked the great
citadel of Troy.

48
00:03:23.403 --> 00:03:25.973
Home. then.

49
00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:27.542
Lest I have not honored the gods

50
00:03:27.608 --> 00:03:30.477
enough to receive
the reward I deserve.

51
00:03:33.181 --> 00:03:35.983
Greetings. Odysseus.

52
00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:36.984
The good man.

53
00:03:38.686 --> 00:03:40.922
Goddess on high.

54
00:03:40.988 --> 00:03:42.322
Clever. maybe.

55
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:44.058
Clever is better than good.

56
00:03:44.125 --> 00:03:45.325
Not just clever.

57
00:03:46.393 --> 00:03:50.164
Brutal. decisive.
and ingenious.

58
00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.901
Hiding your soldiers
in the gift of a wooden horse.

59
00:03:53.968 --> 00:03:55.435
your Trojan horse.

60
00:03:55.503 --> 00:03:58.506
Taking the city by surprise
from the inside out.

61
00:03:58.573 --> 00:03:59.974
Your greatest work.

62
00:04:00.041 --> 00:04:02.143
It did what it was made to do.

63
00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:03.811
But I cannot look behind.

64
00:04:03.878 --> 00:04:06.581
As any craftsman
worth his salt. I pray

65
00:04:06.647 --> 00:04:09.282
that my greatest
work lies ahead.

66
00:04:09.349 --> 00:04:11.451
Perhaps it does.

67
00:04:11.519 --> 00:04:15.690
So home. then. Ithaca.
To your wife.

68
00:04:15.757 --> 00:04:16.758
Your city.

69
00:04:16.824 --> 00:04:19.359
Yes. the only
journey worth the fight.

70
00:04:19.426 --> 00:04:21.294
Are you coming with me. Athena?

71
00:04:21.361 --> 00:04:23.598
Or is there another
reason for this visit?

72
00:04:23.664 --> 00:04:26.333
I come to bring you a warning.

73
00:04:26.399 --> 00:04:30.437
The gods.
they are fickle. Odysseus.

74
00:04:30.505 --> 00:04:34.341
They will not make your
journey home an easy one.

75
00:04:34.407 --> 00:04:37.779
Your trials will be
their entertainment.

76
00:04:37.845 --> 00:04:40.882
They know now that
you are a clever man.

77
00:04:40.948 --> 00:04:42.717
They are jealous.

78
00:04:42.784 --> 00:04:46.554
They will use this against
you to show their power.

79
00:04:48.256 --> 00:04:50.858
Curse me or bless me.
Goddess on high.

80
00:04:50.925 --> 00:04:53.094
But be quick about it.

81
00:04:53.161 --> 00:04:55.295
In due time.

82
00:04:55.362 --> 00:04:57.698
And so begins your odyssey.

83
00:04:57.765 --> 00:05:00.467
And the game of the gods.

84
00:05:02.270 --> 00:05:04.172
Then pray for me. goddess.

85
00:05:04.238 --> 00:05:06.473
For I must reach home.

86
00:05:06.541 --> 00:05:08.308
For my kingdom.

87
00:05:08.375 --> 00:05:09.342
My everything.

88
00:05:09.409 --> 00:05:12.445
My son. My wife.

89
00:05:12.513 --> 00:05:13.881
My world will be gone.

90
00:05:29.297 --> 00:05:31.431
I am looking for men.

91
00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.668
A crew for a dangerous journey.

92
00:05:35.169 --> 00:05:37.805
One the gods themselves
may turn their will against.

93
00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:44.745
Once I am home.
as king of Ithaca.

94
00:05:44.812 --> 00:05:49.784
I assure you each will
receive a suitable reward.

95
00:05:51.252 --> 00:05:54.856
You will never want for anything
for the rest of your lives.

96
00:05:56.157 --> 00:05:57.992
You have the word
of the king himself.

97
00:06:01.562 --> 00:06:03.965
A generous offer and reward.

98
00:06:04.031 --> 00:06:05.633
But are you as
good as your word?

99
00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:08.669
Polites!

100
00:06:08.736 --> 00:06:10.605
You look a little
bit past your prime.

101
00:06:10.671 --> 00:06:13.040
-By the gods!
-Old man.

102
00:06:13.107 --> 00:06:14.709
After all this time.

103
00:06:14.775 --> 00:06:16.611
All this time and you still
haven't gotten any better

104
00:06:16.677 --> 00:06:18.045
at motivational speeches.

105
00:06:19.446 --> 00:06:22.950
Absolute crickets
from you as well.

106
00:06:23.017 --> 00:06:25.385
This is a man who has saved
my life on numerous occasions.

107
00:06:25.452 --> 00:06:29.090
A debt we have both repaid
each other more than once

108
00:06:29.156 --> 00:06:32.526
in a war that has lasted
more than five years.

109
00:06:35.930 --> 00:06:37.632
Although it's closer to ten now.

110
00:06:42.303 --> 00:06:43.738
But these days.

111
00:06:43.804 --> 00:06:47.541
I am much better collecting
scars than I am glory.

112
00:06:47.608 --> 00:06:50.311
But. you will find plenty
of much younger.

113
00:06:50.378 --> 00:06:53.347
probably not as bright men
more than willing to join you.

114
00:06:53.413 --> 00:06:54.982
But probably not here.

115
00:06:55.049 --> 00:06:57.285
sipping goblets in
the middle of the day.

116
00:06:57.351 --> 00:06:58.686
And the rest here.

117
00:06:58.753 --> 00:07:00.354
well. they know not
the true cost of war.

118
00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:02.757
though they may be eager.

119
00:07:02.823 --> 00:07:04.859
-As once we were.
-As we once were.

120
00:07:04.926 --> 00:07:08.129
Listening to our fathers
and our grandfathers stories.

121
00:07:08.195 --> 00:07:11.399
And just more than
willing to prove ourselves.

122
00:07:11.464 --> 00:07:12.967
Can I trust them?

123
00:07:13.034 --> 00:07:14.802
About as much as
you can trust me.

124
00:07:16.304 --> 00:07:19.106
All I know is that what's
waiting for you back in Ithaca.

125
00:07:19.173 --> 00:07:20.440
now that is your reward.

126
00:07:20.508 --> 00:07:22.076
And you deserve it. too.

127
00:07:22.143 --> 00:07:23.144
But for the rest of us...

128
00:07:26.414 --> 00:07:29.750
Join me.
I need men who I can trust.

129
00:07:29.817 --> 00:07:31.953
Men with
experience in battle.

130
00:07:32.019 --> 00:07:33.621
No. no. no. I will not be
going to any battle.

131
00:07:33.688 --> 00:07:35.256
Or any wars.
Ever again.

132
00:07:35.323 --> 00:07:37.625
I am unpersuadable.
I cannot be persuaded.

133
00:07:37.692 --> 00:07:40.528
Did I mention the gold?

134
00:07:40.594 --> 00:07:43.164
Well. did I mention
unpersuaded?

135
00:07:43.230 --> 00:07:44.198
When do we start?

136
00:07:44.265 --> 00:07:45.266
As soon as we recruit two more.

137
00:07:45.333 --> 00:07:46.499
-Two more?
-Yes.

138
00:07:46.567 --> 00:07:48.869
-Okay. Let's go.
-Let's do this.

139
00:07:49.804 --> 00:07:51.672
Alkimos the Navigator.

140
00:07:51.739 --> 00:07:55.176
From what I heard. he was
the one that saved a ship

141
00:07:55.242 --> 00:07:56.978
of fishermen from a cyclone.

142
00:07:57.044 --> 00:07:58.512
Really?

143
00:07:58.579 --> 00:08:01.481
I've heard of you.
King Odysseus.

144
00:08:01.549 --> 00:08:03.517
What have you heard?

145
00:08:03.584 --> 00:08:06.620
That you. sacker of cities.
son of Laertes.

146
00:08:06.687 --> 00:08:08.990
are favored by the gods.

147
00:08:09.056 --> 00:08:13.327
Not all the gods.
One or two. Maybe less.

148
00:08:13.394 --> 00:08:15.162
You survived the Trojan War.

149
00:08:15.229 --> 00:08:16.764
You're a king.

150
00:08:16.831 --> 00:08:18.866
The King of Ithaca.

151
00:08:18.933 --> 00:08:20.868
I have a family
that comes from Ithaca.

152
00:08:20.935 --> 00:08:23.471
I haven't seen them
since I was little.

153
00:08:23.537 --> 00:08:24.472
You know. my king--

154
00:08:24.538 --> 00:08:25.940
I'm not king today.

155
00:08:28.709 --> 00:08:30.244
But if you help me
get home. I will be.

156
00:08:34.849 --> 00:08:37.351
I'm a good navigator.

157
00:08:37.418 --> 00:08:39.186
But you mentioned gold.

158
00:08:39.253 --> 00:08:40.488
Did I?

159
00:08:40.554 --> 00:08:43.057
Oh. You did. Yes.
You mentioned gold.

160
00:08:43.124 --> 00:08:44.525
He mentioned gold.

161
00:08:44.592 --> 00:08:45.593
Hmm.

162
00:08:45.659 --> 00:08:47.661
I don't seek gold.

163
00:08:47.728 --> 00:08:49.563
I'm bored.

164
00:08:49.630 --> 00:08:51.699
Bored of fishing
boats filled with old men

165
00:08:51.766 --> 00:08:54.135
with putrid smelling cargo.

166
00:08:56.404 --> 00:08:57.506
I seek adventure.

167
00:08:57.571 --> 00:08:59.240
New shores.

168
00:08:59.306 --> 00:09:01.409
Like in the stories.

169
00:09:01.475 --> 00:09:02.743
Stories about you.

170
00:09:07.615 --> 00:09:09.183
Then join me.

171
00:09:09.250 --> 00:09:12.353
and we will make stories
that they will never forget.

172
00:09:12.420 --> 00:09:16.357
And I promise you. it will
be anything but boring.

173
00:09:16.424 --> 00:09:19.693
And once we reach Ithaca.
you can join my guard

174
00:09:19.760 --> 00:09:23.064
and help me protect
our fair kingdom.

175
00:09:23.130 --> 00:09:24.065
My king.

176
00:09:25.866 --> 00:09:27.802
Now. how are you at fighting?

177
00:09:27.868 --> 00:09:29.203
I can handle my own.

178
00:09:29.270 --> 00:09:31.138
But if you want a
force to be reckoned with.

179
00:09:31.205 --> 00:09:33.174
you want to
recruit Eurylochus.

180
00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:35.609
I've never seen another
man fight quite like he has.

181
00:09:38.145 --> 00:09:40.848
We'll pay him a visit next.

182
00:09:44.085 --> 00:09:46.153
So what say you. Eurylochus?

183
00:09:46.220 --> 00:09:49.156
I have killed a lot of
men to protect my home.

184
00:09:49.223 --> 00:09:51.859
War has plagued our
country for many years.

185
00:09:55.663 --> 00:09:57.331
How are you at sea?

186
00:09:57.398 --> 00:10:00.569
I'm a fast swimmer. and
even faster with a sword.

187
00:10:00.634 --> 00:10:02.269
Hm. Is that so?

188
00:10:02.336 --> 00:10:03.637
Hm.

189
00:10:04.805 --> 00:10:06.173
But now that
the war is over.

190
00:10:06.240 --> 00:10:08.742
I've found work at a
vineyard up the road.

191
00:10:08.809 --> 00:10:10.845
The owner. he treats me well.

192
00:10:10.911 --> 00:10:15.483
And his daughter.
Talia. she's...

193
00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:19.487
I just don't know if I can
commit to a journey this long.

194
00:10:19.554 --> 00:10:23.724
You will be in Ithaca
before sundown two days hence.

195
00:10:23.791 --> 00:10:25.726
We have to be.

196
00:10:25.793 --> 00:10:27.995
And if you decide to
stay in our fair kingdom.

197
00:10:28.062 --> 00:10:30.998
you will live a life
of ease in Ithaca.

198
00:10:31.065 --> 00:10:33.801
And once there.
she can join you.

199
00:10:36.237 --> 00:10:38.072
If you teach me
how to be as fast

200
00:10:38.139 --> 00:10:40.374
as you. my king
Odysseus. then I'm in.

201
00:10:44.245 --> 00:10:46.313
And as I promised...

202
00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:47.748
We need gold.

203
00:10:47.815 --> 00:10:50.451
You said we need to
be to Ithaca in two days.

204
00:10:50.519 --> 00:10:53.654
Yes. I have a plan.

205
00:10:53.721 --> 00:10:55.089
But you must trust me.

206
00:10:56.625 --> 00:10:58.092
I'm with you to
the end. my king.

207
00:11:00.194 --> 00:11:01.762
Or thereabouts.

208
00:11:01.829 --> 00:11:06.100
<i>From Troy. Odysseus</i>
<i>launched his journey home</i>

209
00:11:06.167 --> 00:11:08.702
<i>with 12 ships and 600 men.</i>

210
00:11:10.237 --> 00:11:14.141
<i>At home in Ithaca.</i>
<i>Odysseus's dear wife Penelope</i>

211
00:11:14.208 --> 00:11:16.977
<i>dreams of her love</i>
<i>bearing the brutal seas</i>

212
00:11:17.044 --> 00:11:19.013
<i>to find his way home to her.</i>

213
00:11:46.307 --> 00:11:47.341
Odysseus?

214
00:12:06.493 --> 00:12:07.728
God's above.

215
00:12:09.830 --> 00:12:12.199
You've shown me Odysseus lives.

216
00:12:14.068 --> 00:12:15.736
Now bring him home.

217
00:12:17.338 --> 00:12:20.274
Bring him home now.
or these lips

218
00:12:20.341 --> 00:12:23.511
shall never again
speak your names.

219
00:12:41.862 --> 00:12:43.632
A growing boy needs food.

220
00:12:43.698 --> 00:12:46.834
A boy needs many things.
mother. but I am not a boy.

221
00:12:46.900 --> 00:12:48.369
Not any...

222
00:12:50.705 --> 00:12:51.673
Mother.

223
00:12:51.740 --> 00:12:53.874
I've seen him. Telemachus.

224
00:12:53.941 --> 00:12:55.042
I've seen your father.

225
00:12:55.109 --> 00:12:56.745
You're bleeding.
You must sit.

226
00:12:56.810 --> 00:12:59.514
No. my son.
We must stand and fight.

227
00:12:59.581 --> 00:13:01.081
What have you seen?

228
00:13:02.550 --> 00:13:03.484
A vision.

229
00:13:06.987 --> 00:13:08.155
A message from the gods.

230
00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:12.727
Troy burns.

231
00:13:12.793 --> 00:13:15.195
Your father. he is triumphant.

232
00:13:15.262 --> 00:13:18.098
He is coming home. but it
may not be fast enough.

233
00:13:18.165 --> 00:13:21.168
Ithaca is vulnerable now.

234
00:13:21.235 --> 00:13:22.671
Now that the war is over.

235
00:13:22.737 --> 00:13:26.006
Odysseus must return to
reclaim the throne. otherwise

236
00:13:26.073 --> 00:13:29.310
another can claim this
kingdom as his own.

237
00:13:29.376 --> 00:13:33.581
Your father would rather
die than let that happen.

238
00:13:33.648 --> 00:13:35.149
He will return.
He must.

239
00:13:35.215 --> 00:13:38.419
And in his absence.
I am the man of this house.

240
00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:40.454
and I say that we...

241
00:13:40.522 --> 00:13:43.123
You will be a man
soon enough. my love. You will.

242
00:13:43.190 --> 00:13:47.328
But you cannot be king.
Not yet.

243
00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:50.431
And therein lies our fight.

244
00:13:52.232 --> 00:13:56.036
Each day that your father
is away. others become

245
00:13:56.103 --> 00:13:59.239
more willing to claim
this kingdom as their own.

246
00:13:59.306 --> 00:14:04.646
If he does not return.
I will not also lose you.

247
00:14:04.713 --> 00:14:07.247
So we must be strong. my son.

248
00:14:07.314 --> 00:14:10.618
Together. we must
be like your father.

249
00:14:11.753 --> 00:14:13.921
Smart and resourceful.

250
00:14:13.987 --> 00:14:17.491
And protect this
kingdom without violence.

251
00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:20.294
Clever.

252
00:14:25.099 --> 00:14:28.202
So clever as to make
the gods jealous.

253
00:14:30.237 --> 00:14:33.240
Whether we want it or not.
the heavens will continue to

254
00:14:33.307 --> 00:14:36.377
move without Odysseus here
by our side where he belongs.

255
00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:40.481
If he does not return soon

256
00:14:40.548 --> 00:14:43.384
after victory
has been declared.

257
00:14:43.450 --> 00:14:46.086
then by law he will have
abandoned his duties as king.

258
00:14:47.988 --> 00:14:51.793
And a suitor. any suitor.

259
00:14:51.860 --> 00:14:54.662
may lay claim to this house.

260
00:14:54.729 --> 00:14:56.430
and to the crown of Ithaca.

261
00:14:56.497 --> 00:14:58.098
And to you.

262
00:14:59.967 --> 00:15:03.137
The law only reaches so far.

263
00:15:03.203 --> 00:15:08.008
When they come.
and come they will.

264
00:15:08.075 --> 00:15:09.711
we must be ready.

265
00:15:09.778 --> 00:15:15.149
And I am ready to fight for you
and for father and the kingdom.

266
00:15:15.215 --> 00:15:18.853
Son. this is not going
to be a sword fight.

267
00:15:18.952 --> 00:15:21.455
Or even a fight of fists.

268
00:15:21.523 --> 00:15:24.458
This will be a fight
of words and propriety.

269
00:15:26.828 --> 00:15:29.096
We need to buy him time.

270
00:15:29.163 --> 00:15:32.966
Keep the suitors busy.

271
00:15:33.033 --> 00:15:35.969
Their bellies full
and distracted.

272
00:15:37.237 --> 00:15:41.543
Now come and honor me
like you do him.

273
00:15:41.609 --> 00:15:44.378
The war is over now.

274
00:15:44.445 --> 00:15:46.480
But our battle
is just beginning.

275
00:15:58.959 --> 00:16:00.628
Goddess Athena...

276
00:16:02.496 --> 00:16:04.398
Help us.

277
00:16:04.465 --> 00:16:05.966
I pray.

278
00:16:06.033 --> 00:16:08.670
But help Odysseus.

279
00:16:08.736 --> 00:16:10.070
Help my father.

280
00:16:11.739 --> 00:16:13.508
Please.

281
00:16:13.575 --> 00:16:15.476
<i>The mighty storm</i>
<i>that struck Odysseus</i>

282
00:16:15.543 --> 00:16:20.915
<i>ravaged the sea for ten days.</i>
<i>taking them far off course.</i>

283
00:16:20.981 --> 00:16:23.283
<i>After battling</i>
<i>the storms at sea.</i>

284
00:16:23.350 --> 00:16:26.788
<i>Odysseus has arrived at</i>
<i>his home in Ithaca...</i>

285
00:16:26.855 --> 00:16:28.188
<i>or so he thought.</i>

286
00:16:28.255 --> 00:16:30.424
This is not Ithaca. Athena!

287
00:16:32.660 --> 00:16:35.996
This is another one
of the gods' cruel jokes.

288
00:16:39.634 --> 00:16:40.568
I must get home.

289
00:16:43.972 --> 00:16:45.472
I will get home.

290
00:16:52.212 --> 00:16:53.347
Penelope.

291
00:16:55.249 --> 00:16:56.518
Sweet Penelope.

292
00:16:58.853 --> 00:17:00.354
I will come home.

293
00:17:04.458 --> 00:17:06.694
Look at you keeping
step with the gods.

294
00:17:10.063 --> 00:17:11.231
Athena.

295
00:17:11.298 --> 00:17:13.500
I am many leagues off course.

296
00:17:13.568 --> 00:17:17.070
I'm only two days
journey from Ithaca.

297
00:17:17.137 --> 00:17:18.773
Please.

298
00:17:18.840 --> 00:17:22.342
Spirit me home to Ithaca.
great goddess.

299
00:17:22.409 --> 00:17:24.478
You know that I cannot.

300
00:17:24.546 --> 00:17:27.849
It is not within
my power to do so.

301
00:17:27.916 --> 00:17:29.918
But think. Odysseus.

302
00:17:29.984 --> 00:17:33.755
Perhaps there is a reason
that you are not yet home.

303
00:17:33.821 --> 00:17:36.791
The gods have another plan.

304
00:17:36.858 --> 00:17:37.792
I see.

305
00:17:40.895 --> 00:17:42.931
I am here to help.

306
00:17:42.997 --> 00:17:46.768
I can offer you help three
times along your journey.

307
00:17:46.834 --> 00:17:48.937
Three gifts.

308
00:17:49.003 --> 00:17:50.304
Only three?

309
00:17:50.370 --> 00:17:52.406
'Tis all I am permitted.

310
00:17:52.472 --> 00:17:54.842
I am helping because
I see myself

311
00:17:54.909 --> 00:17:58.546
in your clever mind and
your tactician's brain.

312
00:17:58.613 --> 00:18:02.215
Your glory in
the Trojan War honors me.

313
00:18:02.282 --> 00:18:05.185
And that is why I will help you.

314
00:18:05.252 --> 00:18:06.754
I am flattered. goddess.

315
00:18:08.590 --> 00:18:09.524
I must decline.

316
00:18:11.258 --> 00:18:12.827
I am offended.

317
00:18:12.894 --> 00:18:17.065
Odysseus.
Refusing a gift from the gods?

318
00:18:17.130 --> 00:18:19.099
From Athena herself.

319
00:18:19.166 --> 00:18:22.436
If you cannot spirit
me home then please

320
00:18:22.503 --> 00:18:28.042
understand I must ask for
help only when I need it.

321
00:18:28.108 --> 00:18:33.280
When all hope is lost. my wits
abandon me and death beckons.

322
00:18:35.248 --> 00:18:38.418
In this moment I will
honor your generosity

323
00:18:38.485 --> 00:18:41.254
for I know the
value of godly gifts.

324
00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:46.193
Then you must know even now

325
00:18:46.259 --> 00:18:49.296
dogs are sniffing
at your house

326
00:18:49.363 --> 00:18:51.231
and at your wife.

327
00:18:52.567 --> 00:18:56.236
The gods are testing
your cleverness. Odysseus.

328
00:18:58.806 --> 00:19:01.509
Then I pray the
gods do not stall me

329
00:19:01.576 --> 00:19:03.544
any longer than
they already have.

330
00:19:06.080 --> 00:19:08.116
Go. hero.

331
00:19:08.181 --> 00:19:10.417
Honor me and prove your worth.

332
00:19:11.318 --> 00:19:12.887
Get home.

333
00:19:12.954 --> 00:19:16.591
No matter what horrors the
gods place upon your path.

334
00:19:22.496 --> 00:19:26.868
The opportunity here
is too great to pass up.

335
00:19:26.934 --> 00:19:30.071
A kingdom. a crown.

336
00:19:30.138 --> 00:19:32.974
and even the queen herself

337
00:19:33.041 --> 00:19:35.475
all free for the taking.

338
00:19:35.543 --> 00:19:39.614
And it should be easy
enough owing to propriety

339
00:19:39.681 --> 00:19:41.816
and Grecian law.

340
00:19:41.883 --> 00:19:46.054
All suitors
must be taken seriously.

341
00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:48.321
And I will be the first.

342
00:19:49.757 --> 00:19:51.092
Ha!

343
00:19:51.159 --> 00:19:54.562
The early bird gets the kingdom.

344
00:19:56.631 --> 00:20:01.002
She'll have no choice
but to honor my demands.

345
00:20:01.069 --> 00:20:02.537
All of my demands.

346
00:20:14.849 --> 00:20:18.485
Antinous just said
the most awful things.

347
00:20:18.553 --> 00:20:21.923
Threatening to take the crown.
our house. and you!

348
00:20:23.958 --> 00:20:25.292
Then it has begun.

349
00:20:25.358 --> 00:20:28.529
We must be on our
guard. Telemachus.

350
00:20:28.596 --> 00:20:31.364
Always polite and inviting.

351
00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:34.769
But on our guard.

352
00:20:38.573 --> 00:20:40.240
But on our guard!

353
00:20:44.879 --> 00:20:47.849
<i>Perilous winds</i>
<i>take their toll on the voyagers</i>

354
00:20:47.915 --> 00:20:52.553
<i>who now take shore on</i>
<i>a small island. rich in gold.</i>

355
00:20:52.620 --> 00:20:55.089
Is this part of
the plan. Lord Odysseus?

356
00:20:55.156 --> 00:20:56.356
Indeed. Eurylochus.

357
00:20:56.423 --> 00:20:59.259
Now stay close.
and your lips closed.

358
00:21:00.695 --> 00:21:03.765
I don't quite understand
what this has to do with gold.

359
00:21:03.831 --> 00:21:05.633
We're going to retrieve gold.

360
00:21:05.700 --> 00:21:10.505
My gold that was
stolen by a cyclops.

361
00:21:10.571 --> 00:21:14.208
He's the son of Poseidon.
God of the sea.

362
00:21:14.274 --> 00:21:15.743
A real cyclops?

363
00:21:15.810 --> 00:21:17.245
Why didn't you tell us sooner?

364
00:21:17.310 --> 00:21:18.713
They eat people. so I've heard.

365
00:21:18.780 --> 00:21:20.982
My brave crew...

366
00:21:21.048 --> 00:21:22.784
Alkimos. you wanted adventure.

367
00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:24.218
Here it is.

368
00:21:24.284 --> 00:21:29.157
Eurylochus. you wanted to stay
alive in a cave with a Cyclops.

369
00:21:29.223 --> 00:21:30.591
You must learn to be faster.

370
00:21:30.658 --> 00:21:33.360
And Polites.
now you wanted gold.

371
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:39.000
Yes. this cyclops has
been hoarding gold for years.

372
00:21:39.066 --> 00:21:40.735
Mine and others.

373
00:21:40.802 --> 00:21:43.738
And it's that gold that's
going to help us get a ship.

374
00:21:43.805 --> 00:21:47.440
He's been terrorizing this
mountainside for many years.

375
00:21:47.508 --> 00:21:48.876
It's time we return the favor.

376
00:21:50.878 --> 00:21:55.315
Today. our journey
begins with a cyclops.

377
00:21:55.382 --> 00:21:58.019
Or it ends before it begins.

378
00:21:58.085 --> 00:21:59.954
Now who's with me?

379
00:22:00.021 --> 00:22:01.122
My king.

380
00:22:01.189 --> 00:22:02.790
Help! Help!

381
00:22:04.158 --> 00:22:05.593
Help! Help!

382
00:22:19.040 --> 00:22:20.741
He... He ate him.

383
00:22:22.043 --> 00:22:26.814
Do as I say when I say.
then we will win the day.

384
00:22:26.881 --> 00:22:28.415
All right. what's the plan?

385
00:22:28.481 --> 00:22:30.251
We'll circle the
base of the mountain.

386
00:22:30.318 --> 00:22:32.153
Go inside.

387
00:22:32.220 --> 00:22:34.755
Stay close. and downwind.

388
00:22:34.822 --> 00:22:38.059
Cyclops. he can smell
us nearly a league away.

389
00:22:39.594 --> 00:22:40.728
Hold. hold. hold.

390
00:22:44.065 --> 00:22:47.367
At Troy. during the
war. you were there?

391
00:22:47.434 --> 00:22:49.670
I sure was.

392
00:22:49.737 --> 00:22:51.172
I barely survived.
and I probably wouldn't have

393
00:22:51.239 --> 00:22:53.307
if it weren't for Odysseus.

394
00:22:53.373 --> 00:22:56.277
Saved me from
an entire garrison.

395
00:22:56.344 --> 00:22:58.012
Picked them off one by one.

396
00:22:58.079 --> 00:23:00.781
Hiding in the shadows.
which is a pretty big

397
00:23:00.848 --> 00:23:03.651
feat for him. considering
he's a big bastard.

398
00:23:03.718 --> 00:23:06.020
I've only heard stories.

399
00:23:06.087 --> 00:23:07.154
Legends. really.

400
00:23:07.221 --> 00:23:10.124
Well. not everything
you hear is true.

401
00:23:10.191 --> 00:23:13.060
Only half of what
I just said was true.

402
00:23:13.127 --> 00:23:14.695
Is he as good a man as they say?

403
00:23:14.762 --> 00:23:17.231
He's a great man. though
he'd never admit it.

404
00:23:17.298 --> 00:23:19.133
But out of humility.

405
00:23:19.200 --> 00:23:22.336
He's a man who
values many virtues.

406
00:23:22.402 --> 00:23:27.174
But the one he values above
all others is cleverness.

407
00:23:27.241 --> 00:23:32.914
You see. a good man engenders
himself to friends. family.

408
00:23:32.980 --> 00:23:37.450
A clever man.
a clever man survives.

409
00:23:37.518 --> 00:23:38.653
Quickly. now.

410
00:23:41.622 --> 00:23:45.092
Gods willing. we will. too.

411
00:23:56.337 --> 00:23:59.807
Keep your eyes open and
your wits about you. man.

412
00:23:59.874 --> 00:24:03.144
Odysseus. you know
no-ones actually entered

413
00:24:03.210 --> 00:24:06.948
the Cyclops cave and
lived to tell the tale.

414
00:24:07.014 --> 00:24:08.549
Not until today they don't.

415
00:24:12.954 --> 00:24:15.890
He will be busy
with his guests.

416
00:24:17.091 --> 00:24:19.327
This is our chance.

417
00:24:19.393 --> 00:24:21.595
We sneak in.
find the treasure.

418
00:24:21.662 --> 00:24:24.532
take what we can carry.
stay quiet.

419
00:24:24.598 --> 00:24:27.902
get out the same way.

420
00:24:27.969 --> 00:24:29.837
Stay with me.

421
00:24:29.904 --> 00:24:30.838
Stay low.

422
00:24:39.213 --> 00:24:40.748
But how do we find the treasure?

423
00:24:42.616 --> 00:24:44.952
Where does the cyclops
even keep its treasure?

424
00:24:46.921 --> 00:24:50.591
It smells like death.

425
00:24:50.658 --> 00:24:52.960
What better place to
hide your gold than in

426
00:24:53.027 --> 00:24:57.798
a place that smells so bad
that no one dares enter?

427
00:24:57.865 --> 00:25:00.601
Use your nose.
Follow its direction.

428
00:25:00.668 --> 00:25:05.639
Is... Is somebody here?

429
00:25:05.706 --> 00:25:09.143
I smell...
I smell men.

430
00:25:09.210 --> 00:25:12.680
I smell your fear.

431
00:25:12.747 --> 00:25:16.751
You can't...
You can't hide for long

432
00:25:16.817 --> 00:25:21.422
and Polyphemus.
the son of Poseidon.

433
00:25:21.489 --> 00:25:25.192
is still hungry.

434
00:25:27.428 --> 00:25:28.696
There.

435
00:25:28.763 --> 00:25:30.631
The smell of the
worst is that way.

436
00:25:30.698 --> 00:25:31.966
Move. move.

437
00:25:49.216 --> 00:25:50.284
Let's move.

438
00:26:03.097 --> 00:26:04.231
Quiet.

439
00:26:11.672 --> 00:26:13.040
Holy gold.

440
00:26:14.108 --> 00:26:15.544
Reward.

441
00:26:15.609 --> 00:26:17.244
Rewards for good men.

442
00:26:17.311 --> 00:26:19.080
Shh.

443
00:26:19.146 --> 00:26:20.281
Okay. quickly.

444
00:26:20.347 --> 00:26:21.882
Take everything you can.

445
00:26:21.949 --> 00:26:25.554
Actually. only what you can
carry. just like Odysseus said.

446
00:26:25.619 --> 00:26:27.556
Wait. where is Odysseus?

447
00:26:27.621 --> 00:26:30.291
Odysseus is gone.

448
00:26:30.357 --> 00:26:32.527
You've come for my gold!

449
00:26:32.593 --> 00:26:33.861
Shh!

450
00:26:33.928 --> 00:26:37.298
-Thieves!
-Okay. take cover!

451
00:26:41.368 --> 00:26:43.938
Thieves. who are you?

452
00:26:46.207 --> 00:26:47.708
We're nobody!

453
00:26:49.944 --> 00:26:52.046
Grab the treasure! Run!

454
00:27:01.755 --> 00:27:03.724
Go! I'll keep him busy!

455
00:27:05.527 --> 00:27:08.629
We fight with you.
my king!

456
00:27:14.435 --> 00:27:15.636
Eurylochus!

457
00:27:16.505 --> 00:27:17.606
Odysseus!

458
00:27:17.671 --> 00:27:19.073
Polites. help! Ah!

459
00:27:21.675 --> 00:27:24.478
No! No!

460
00:27:24.546 --> 00:27:27.181
You will die. foul beast!

461
00:27:27.248 --> 00:27:28.916
For Eurylochus!

462
00:27:32.453 --> 00:27:34.188
Nobody?

463
00:27:34.255 --> 00:27:35.723
It calls for help.

464
00:27:36.824 --> 00:27:38.792
No one will come!

465
00:27:38.859 --> 00:27:41.362
It calls out for nobody.

466
00:27:41.428 --> 00:27:42.363
No one will come.

467
00:27:47.201 --> 00:27:50.738
May the gods bless
you. Eurylochus.

468
00:27:50.804 --> 00:27:52.973
and speed you
through the underworld

469
00:27:53.040 --> 00:27:56.677
as quickly as
the gods will permit.

470
00:27:56.744 --> 00:27:59.413
Now. go.
Grab the treasure.

471
00:27:59.480 --> 00:28:02.617
The son of Poseidon will
not lick his wounds long.

472
00:28:02.683 --> 00:28:04.051
Go!

473
00:28:04.118 --> 00:28:06.555
-Only take what we need.
-Only take what we need.

474
00:28:06.621 --> 00:28:08.489
Yes. enough for a boat.

475
00:28:08.557 --> 00:28:10.090
Provisions and no more.

476
00:28:10.157 --> 00:28:11.892
Okay. here's a bit of gold.
There's a bit of this...

477
00:28:11.959 --> 00:28:13.360
-Hurry!
-Yes. grab that.

478
00:28:13.427 --> 00:28:16.697
That's expensive. I like that.
Okay. and...

479
00:28:16.764 --> 00:28:18.766
Okay. let's go.

480
00:28:18.832 --> 00:28:21.302
-Go!
-I got it. I got it. I got it.

481
00:28:31.613 --> 00:28:32.913
Charie!

482
00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:36.016
And greetings to the
great house of Odysseus.

483
00:28:36.083 --> 00:28:38.452
Greetings to you. traveler.

484
00:28:38.520 --> 00:28:41.288
Your voice seems so...

485
00:28:41.355 --> 00:28:42.890
familiar.

486
00:28:42.957 --> 00:28:45.226
But our house is
in no condition...

487
00:28:45.292 --> 00:28:48.262
Aye. aye.
Well met. my lord Telemachus.

488
00:28:48.329 --> 00:28:49.830
Telemachus.

489
00:28:51.432 --> 00:28:54.368
Apologies. Apologies.

490
00:28:54.435 --> 00:28:56.671
I am Antinous.

491
00:28:56.737 --> 00:29:00.675
And I come bearing gifts.

492
00:29:00.741 --> 00:29:03.944
The gift of my protection.

493
00:29:05.779 --> 00:29:07.781
A gracious home.

494
00:29:07.848 --> 00:29:09.917
A kingly estate. indeed.

495
00:29:17.124 --> 00:29:20.461
Ready our ship. men.
We leave port immediately.

496
00:29:20.528 --> 00:29:21.495
-My king.
-My king.

497
00:29:39.179 --> 00:29:41.549
Come to wish us farewell?

498
00:29:41.616 --> 00:29:42.751
I have.

499
00:29:42.816 --> 00:29:45.520
And I come bearing a gift.

500
00:29:45.587 --> 00:29:49.456
A bag of wind
to speed you along your journey.

501
00:29:49.524 --> 00:29:51.492
Perhaps if you'd
accepted my offer of help.

502
00:29:51.559 --> 00:29:54.596
and asked for stronger
and faster ships.

503
00:29:54.663 --> 00:29:56.196
you would not need it.

504
00:29:56.263 --> 00:29:59.433
Or you would already
be closer to home.

505
00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:00.568
My ship.

506
00:30:00.635 --> 00:30:03.203
I would not trust
a boat from the gods.

507
00:30:03.270 --> 00:30:08.409
Who knows if the previous owners
seek revenge and come find me?

508
00:30:08.475 --> 00:30:11.111
And what of the previous
owners of this treasure?

509
00:30:13.180 --> 00:30:14.882
My ship.

510
00:30:14.948 --> 00:30:16.183
My treasure.

511
00:30:16.250 --> 00:30:17.351
My men.

512
00:30:22.524 --> 00:30:23.924
What's left of them.

513
00:30:32.399 --> 00:30:33.901
By Olympus.

514
00:30:36.236 --> 00:30:38.138
One of the gods
speaking to Odysseus.

515
00:30:40.508 --> 00:30:41.609
Gifts.

516
00:30:41.676 --> 00:30:43.277
Gifts from the gods themselves.

517
00:30:46.146 --> 00:30:48.616
It's a generous gift.

518
00:30:48.683 --> 00:30:50.552
And I accept your bag of wind.

519
00:30:50.618 --> 00:30:54.589
But it is not one of your
three gifts until I use it.

520
00:30:54.656 --> 00:30:56.990
Why not use it now?

521
00:30:57.057 --> 00:30:58.660
I will use it.

522
00:30:58.727 --> 00:31:01.395
But I will use it when I must.

523
00:31:01.462 --> 00:31:04.566
The gifts of a god
come with a heavy price.

524
00:31:07.736 --> 00:31:10.938
Hurry home. son of Laertes.

525
00:31:11.004 --> 00:31:12.306
Honor me.

526
00:31:16.243 --> 00:31:17.177
Rewards.

527
00:31:24.451 --> 00:31:26.788
Odysseus!

528
00:31:26.855 --> 00:31:27.822
Was that...

529
00:31:27.921 --> 00:31:29.189
Athena herself.

530
00:31:29.256 --> 00:31:31.258
Come to wish us a farewell.

531
00:31:32.493 --> 00:31:33.762
Could she help us?

532
00:31:33.828 --> 00:31:36.096
Help us get there faster.

533
00:31:36.163 --> 00:31:37.431
I would give my life
many times over if it

534
00:31:37.498 --> 00:31:39.967
meant getting home
sooner to my loved ones.

535
00:31:40.033 --> 00:31:43.605
But the gods play
dangerous games with men.

536
00:31:43.671 --> 00:31:47.174
They could spirit us home
with just a mere thought.

537
00:31:47.241 --> 00:31:49.276
Or the breath from their lungs.

538
00:31:49.343 --> 00:31:52.714
Or they could smite us where we
stand and send us to our dooms.

539
00:31:52.781 --> 00:31:55.249
To them. it's all the same.

540
00:31:55.315 --> 00:31:57.184
That's why we
must tread lightly.

541
00:31:57.251 --> 00:32:00.555
Especially with the ones
who seem the most generous.

542
00:32:00.622 --> 00:32:02.055
And what of that?

543
00:32:02.122 --> 00:32:03.725
Is that a gift?
A reward?

544
00:32:03.792 --> 00:32:05.627
No. it's nothing.

545
00:32:05.693 --> 00:32:07.127
It's a good luck charm.

546
00:32:07.194 --> 00:32:09.430
Now. Polites. let's go home.

547
00:32:20.240 --> 00:32:21.743
A guest in my home.

548
00:32:21.810 --> 00:32:24.579
Aye. but not just any guest.

549
00:32:24.646 --> 00:32:26.514
Antinous. my queen.

550
00:32:26.581 --> 00:32:28.482
At your service.

551
00:32:28.550 --> 00:32:30.150
Well met. Antinous.

552
00:32:30.217 --> 00:32:33.353
And to what do we
owe this generous visit?

553
00:32:33.420 --> 00:32:38.258
I come to pay my respects
to the great Odysseus himself.

554
00:32:38.325 --> 00:32:41.228
And to those he left behind.

555
00:32:41.295 --> 00:32:43.197
He will return. He...

556
00:32:43.263 --> 00:32:44.465
And we accept that respect

557
00:32:44.532 --> 00:32:46.433
in the spirit
that it was given.

558
00:32:48.937 --> 00:32:50.270
Thank you. Antinous.

559
00:32:52.105 --> 00:32:56.511
And I am here to confirm
that this home is safe.

560
00:32:56.578 --> 00:33:01.048
Safe from any who might think
to encroach upon its sanctity.

561
00:33:01.114 --> 00:33:04.051
And to offer my
allegiance and my duty to you

562
00:33:04.117 --> 00:33:06.721
and yours
and to this kingdom.

563
00:33:08.322 --> 00:33:12.059
And to offer my services
to you

564
00:33:12.125 --> 00:33:15.496
as husband and father...

565
00:33:18.666 --> 00:33:19.701
and king.

566
00:33:19.767 --> 00:33:21.001
There is no need for that.

567
00:33:21.068 --> 00:33:22.002
Or for you. My father--

568
00:33:22.069 --> 00:33:24.004
You'll forgive my son.

569
00:33:24.071 --> 00:33:27.040
He can be rather spirited.

570
00:33:31.646 --> 00:33:33.013
Much like his father.

571
00:33:34.248 --> 00:33:37.117
A generous proposal. indeed.

572
00:33:37.184 --> 00:33:40.320
But we have only just met.

573
00:33:40.387 --> 00:33:42.624
Perhaps we can get
better acquainted first.

574
00:33:44.592 --> 00:33:46.861
A fair suggestion.

575
00:33:46.928 --> 00:33:48.195
Right and good.

576
00:33:48.262 --> 00:33:51.866
But I have to admit.
my gracious queen.

577
00:33:51.933 --> 00:33:54.067
I am famished.

578
00:33:54.134 --> 00:33:59.574
And my lips are parched from
my long journey to your door.

579
00:33:59.641 --> 00:34:03.778
Yes. Refreshments might
do us all some good.

580
00:34:06.814 --> 00:34:07.782
Telemachus.

581
00:34:09.182 --> 00:34:10.585
I could use your help.

582
00:34:14.856 --> 00:34:15.823
Take your time.

583
00:34:17.090 --> 00:34:18.560
Take your time.

584
00:34:20.093 --> 00:34:21.563
I'm in no rush.

585
00:34:24.532 --> 00:34:26.199
Mother. what are you doing?

586
00:34:26.266 --> 00:34:28.168
My duty. my son.

587
00:34:28.235 --> 00:34:31.371
And I expect you to do the same.

588
00:34:31.438 --> 00:34:32.640
Antinous is our guest.

589
00:34:32.707 --> 00:34:34.809
Antinous is a
lecherous fool who...

590
00:34:38.713 --> 00:34:39.647
Mother. I--

591
00:34:39.714 --> 00:34:43.116
There will be
other fools. son.

592
00:34:43.183 --> 00:34:44.519
He is merely the first.

593
00:34:44.586 --> 00:34:47.021
It's just like I warned you.

594
00:34:47.087 --> 00:34:50.123
Every day Ithaca
goes without a king

595
00:34:50.190 --> 00:34:53.460
and our house without
our dearest love.

596
00:34:53.528 --> 00:34:55.530
we edge closer
and closer to chaos.

597
00:34:57.966 --> 00:35:00.602
While he is here. the others in

598
00:35:00.668 --> 00:35:03.203
waiting will keep
their distance.

599
00:35:05.873 --> 00:35:08.543
Concerned about their chances.
making assumptions...

600
00:35:10.678 --> 00:35:12.580
Peace is kept.

601
00:35:12.647 --> 00:35:14.214
But mother. I don't think...

602
00:35:14.281 --> 00:35:17.217
We keep--
We keep him distracted.

603
00:35:17.284 --> 00:35:19.252
And we buy your father time.

604
00:35:19.319 --> 00:35:21.656
And while we wait
and be polite and

605
00:35:21.723 --> 00:35:25.627
kowtow to that.
any peace we buy

606
00:35:25.693 --> 00:35:26.995
is not guaranteed.

607
00:35:27.061 --> 00:35:28.730
It is all we can do.

608
00:35:30.031 --> 00:35:31.164
For now.

609
00:35:39.040 --> 00:35:40.908
Now. come on.

610
00:35:40.975 --> 00:35:43.310
We mustn't keep our
honored guest waiting.

611
00:35:46.413 --> 00:35:47.882
Steady there. Alkimos.

612
00:35:47.949 --> 00:35:50.752
With any luck. we'll be home
in a day and a half.

613
00:35:54.122 --> 00:35:55.288
My king.

614
00:35:59.493 --> 00:36:01.328
A storm's coming.

615
00:36:01.395 --> 00:36:02.262
Keep it steady. Alkimos.

616
00:36:02.329 --> 00:36:03.931
Put your back into it.

617
00:36:03.998 --> 00:36:06.333
Polites. grab those lines.
We're going to need them.

618
00:36:09.070 --> 00:36:11.304
Poseidon's bad breath.

619
00:36:11.371 --> 00:36:13.240
Poseidon's breath?

620
00:36:13.306 --> 00:36:15.308
Hot air and spit.

621
00:36:15.375 --> 00:36:17.812
That's Poseidon's bad breath.

622
00:36:17.879 --> 00:36:20.848
He must have learned of
the mark I left on his son.

623
00:36:20.915 --> 00:36:23.584
And his ocean is
pushing us off course.

624
00:36:23.651 --> 00:36:24.585
Look. there.

625
00:36:31.626 --> 00:36:34.461
The current.
It turns against us.

626
00:36:34.529 --> 00:36:37.131
Yes.
Adjust your heading.

627
00:36:37.197 --> 00:36:38.900
Into the wind.

628
00:36:38.966 --> 00:36:40.001
-The wind?
-Yes.

629
00:36:40.068 --> 00:36:41.736
My king...

630
00:36:41.803 --> 00:36:44.639
Poseidon's strength is strongest
in the water and the current.

631
00:36:45.973 --> 00:36:48.776
But if we catch the wind
we can use it as our guide.

632
00:36:48.843 --> 00:36:51.879
Polites. fortify the mast
and the sail.

633
00:36:54.115 --> 00:36:57.852
We cannot afford to be
any further from our goal.

634
00:36:57.919 --> 00:37:00.988
My king. the ship...

635
00:37:01.055 --> 00:37:02.322
She can't hold it.

636
00:37:02.389 --> 00:37:04.759
She will do what
we tell her to do.

637
00:37:04.826 --> 00:37:06.794
The wind going one way
and the current the other.

638
00:37:06.861 --> 00:37:08.663
I'm afraid we're
going to be torn apart.

639
00:37:08.730 --> 00:37:11.398
If we catch the wind.
tread lightly.

640
00:37:11.465 --> 00:37:14.635
We can crest the waves
instead of wrestling with them.

641
00:37:17.138 --> 00:37:18.706
Yes.

642
00:37:18.773 --> 00:37:21.542
We must tread lightly if we
want to keep pace with those.

643
00:37:23.177 --> 00:37:27.380
Spit all you want. Poseidon!
I will not be swayed.

644
00:37:27.447 --> 00:37:28.916
Not today. not ever.

645
00:37:30.151 --> 00:37:31.686
Odysseus...

646
00:37:34.387 --> 00:37:35.990
The waves!

647
00:37:36.057 --> 00:37:37.525
The waves. they're coming
right for us.

648
00:37:46.433 --> 00:37:48.870
We've got
to keep her on course!

649
00:37:48.936 --> 00:37:50.437
Try harder.

650
00:37:50.505 --> 00:37:54.208
Come on!
Come on. oh gods. Punish me!

651
00:37:54.274 --> 00:37:55.610
Punish me!

652
00:37:59.680 --> 00:38:01.883
The sea.
she means to turn us over!

653
00:38:04.417 --> 00:38:06.220
-Odysseus.
-Hold tight.

654
00:38:06.286 --> 00:38:08.189
Hold tight. men.
We can steer her.

655
00:38:08.256 --> 00:38:10.091
We'll steer her through this.

656
00:38:10.158 --> 00:38:12.492
And through the underworld.
if need be and back.

657
00:38:17.665 --> 00:38:19.167
We're not strong enough.

658
00:38:19.233 --> 00:38:21.035
We're not going to make it.

659
00:38:21.102 --> 00:38:23.303
The sea shall eat us all.

660
00:38:23.370 --> 00:38:25.573
The wind.
The wind's too strong.

661
00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:27.340
We're going to lose the sail.

662
00:38:27.407 --> 00:38:30.645
No. No. it's not too strong.
It's the strength we need.

663
00:38:31.612 --> 00:38:33.581
Hand me those lines.

664
00:38:40.621 --> 00:38:43.858
Pull the oar.
Pull with all your might!

665
00:38:43.925 --> 00:38:44.926
Pull!

666
00:38:44.992 --> 00:38:46.627
If we lose the oar.
we're done for.

667
00:38:46.694 --> 00:38:49.864
If we do not act now. we die.

668
00:38:49.931 --> 00:38:50.998
Pull the oar!

669
00:38:55.368 --> 00:38:56.604
Pull it!

670
00:38:58.739 --> 00:39:01.809
That's it. That's it!

671
00:39:01.876 --> 00:39:03.845
The wind is the
strength we need.

672
00:39:09.517 --> 00:39:10.651
It's working.

673
00:39:23.865 --> 00:39:26.234
Odysseus.

674
00:39:26.300 --> 00:39:27.268
Wind.

675
00:39:27.335 --> 00:39:29.369
Wind and water.

676
00:39:29.436 --> 00:39:31.606
They are nothing.

677
00:39:31.672 --> 00:39:34.407
They are nothing
when Ithaca waits for us.

678
00:39:39.614 --> 00:39:42.415
I'm coming home.

679
00:39:42.482 --> 00:39:44.051
I am coming home.

680
00:39:53.160 --> 00:39:55.363
So then...

681
00:39:55.428 --> 00:39:56.931
Queen Penelope.

682
00:39:58.232 --> 00:40:00.234
Antinous.

683
00:40:00.301 --> 00:40:02.136
Do you have need of more food?

684
00:40:02.203 --> 00:40:03.838
Or drink perhaps?

685
00:40:06.674 --> 00:40:09.409
Both. Please.

686
00:40:11.512 --> 00:40:13.514
Your wine.

687
00:40:13.581 --> 00:40:15.683
It has a lovely bouquet.

688
00:40:20.087 --> 00:40:22.623
A noble vintage indeed.

689
00:40:22.690 --> 00:40:25.159
A captivating aroma.

690
00:40:25.226 --> 00:40:27.460
And sweet acidity.

691
00:40:27.528 --> 00:40:29.429
It is rich.

692
00:40:29.496 --> 00:40:31.065
And full bodied.

693
00:40:34.101 --> 00:40:35.603
Just like you.

694
00:40:37.371 --> 00:40:39.439
You do flatter me. Antinous.

695
00:40:41.309 --> 00:40:42.643
Maybe I do.

696
00:40:44.812 --> 00:40:46.514
But...

697
00:40:46.580 --> 00:40:48.115
I worry...

698
00:40:48.182 --> 00:40:52.353
The time for flattery
has passed.

699
00:40:52.420 --> 00:40:55.189
There will be other suitors

700
00:40:55.256 --> 00:40:57.959
lining up at your door.

701
00:40:58.025 --> 00:40:59.927
And soon...

702
00:40:59.994 --> 00:41:04.365
They will be much
less patient men than I.

703
00:41:04.432 --> 00:41:06.400
And after the suitors

704
00:41:06.466 --> 00:41:08.169
will come the looters.

705
00:41:08.235 --> 00:41:09.870
And then the troublemakers.

706
00:41:11.605 --> 00:41:13.941
And I will be unable
to protect you.

707
00:41:15.509 --> 00:41:16.711
Unless?

708
00:41:16.777 --> 00:41:19.113
Unless I am your husband.

709
00:41:20.548 --> 00:41:22.249
Unless I am king.

710
00:41:25.186 --> 00:41:29.857
I would hate to see anything
unfortunate befall you...

711
00:41:30.725 --> 00:41:34.395
Or your son in such

712
00:41:34.462 --> 00:41:36.831
rudderless times as these.

713
00:41:38.866 --> 00:41:41.969
It is time to make
your choice. Penelope.

714
00:41:45.406 --> 00:41:47.808
Before someone makes it for you.

715
00:42:11.899 --> 00:42:15.002
Alkimos. get some beeswax.

716
00:42:15.069 --> 00:42:17.738
Focus repairs on
the prow of the ship.

717
00:42:17.805 --> 00:42:20.207
That storm really took
a bite out of our hide.

718
00:42:20.274 --> 00:42:23.010
But we need the ship
to have her speed back.

719
00:42:23.077 --> 00:42:24.078
Yes. my king.

720
00:42:26.247 --> 00:42:30.651
The sea herself added another
day and a half to our journey

721
00:42:30.718 --> 00:42:33.587
that we do not have to spare.

722
00:42:33.654 --> 00:42:35.990
The woes of my
heart upon this sea.

723
00:42:38.125 --> 00:42:40.194
What storm do you
think was worse?

724
00:42:40.261 --> 00:42:42.663
The one we just sailed through.
or the one that is on your brow?

725
00:42:44.498 --> 00:42:46.300
The storm to come.

726
00:42:46.367 --> 00:42:47.802
The journey ahead.

727
00:42:47.868 --> 00:42:49.003
The journey home.

728
00:42:50.304 --> 00:42:51.939
Yes.

729
00:42:52.006 --> 00:42:55.142
Polites. is I must get home
no matter what the cost.

730
00:42:55.209 --> 00:42:56.277
I must.

731
00:42:56.343 --> 00:42:58.612
I wonder if the costs
already paid.

732
00:42:58.679 --> 00:43:00.081
No. Polites...

733
00:43:00.147 --> 00:43:02.983
The costs were paid
both here and back in Troy.

734
00:43:04.285 --> 00:43:06.287
With flesh and blood.

735
00:43:06.353 --> 00:43:08.055
And this.
This is our reward. is it?

736
00:43:08.122 --> 00:43:10.324
More hardship.

737
00:43:10.391 --> 00:43:12.059
More storms.
Rough seas.

738
00:43:12.126 --> 00:43:14.595
I cannot control the fates.
Nor the seas.

739
00:43:14.662 --> 00:43:15.796
You forget that
I've seen you

740
00:43:15.863 --> 00:43:17.364
perform miracles
before. Odysseus.

741
00:43:17.431 --> 00:43:19.633
Miracles even
the gods couldn't choose.

742
00:43:19.700 --> 00:43:21.702
If this was my kingdom. yes.

743
00:43:21.769 --> 00:43:23.604
But this is not my kingdom.

744
00:43:23.671 --> 00:43:25.439
Back home in my kingdom--

745
00:43:25.507 --> 00:43:26.707
By the gods of the sea!

746
00:43:31.712 --> 00:43:32.880
The sea has teeth!

747
00:43:39.787 --> 00:43:41.055
By the gods!

748
00:43:41.122 --> 00:43:42.690
Charybdis!

749
00:43:42.756 --> 00:43:45.793
It's another one of Poseidon's
weapons of vengeance.

750
00:43:45.860 --> 00:43:47.828
You didn't stop Poseidon.

751
00:43:47.895 --> 00:43:49.363
You just made him more angry.

752
00:43:53.934 --> 00:43:56.670
Alkimos. come steer.

753
00:43:56.737 --> 00:43:58.239
Steer us around
the outside of it.

754
00:43:58.305 --> 00:44:00.374
My king. the repairs
aren't finished yet.

755
00:44:00.441 --> 00:44:02.544
Without them. we won't
be able to make that turn.

756
00:44:02.611 --> 00:44:03.744
It will be almost impossible.

757
00:44:03.811 --> 00:44:06.380
I will make that turn.
I will.

758
00:44:21.996 --> 00:44:22.963
The sea!

759
00:44:23.030 --> 00:44:24.131
It has swallowed so many.

760
00:44:24.198 --> 00:44:25.966
but I had no idea
it had a mouth!

761
00:44:27.768 --> 00:44:29.770
My king. the winds!

762
00:44:29.837 --> 00:44:30.971
We're losing speed!

763
00:44:33.007 --> 00:44:34.775
Odysseus. what do we do?

764
00:44:34.842 --> 00:44:38.245
We will not let it
dissuade us off our course.

765
00:44:38.312 --> 00:44:39.680
Push. Alkimos!

766
00:44:39.747 --> 00:44:40.981
Push. Polites!

767
00:44:41.048 --> 00:44:42.349
Push!

768
00:44:42.416 --> 00:44:46.253
We will ride the wind
and the waves to freedom!

769
00:44:46.320 --> 00:44:48.489
Aye. my king!

770
00:44:48.557 --> 00:44:49.658
Odysseus!

771
00:44:51.526 --> 00:44:52.459
Look!

772
00:44:55.696 --> 00:44:57.898
By the gods!
It follows!

773
00:44:59.400 --> 00:45:02.036
Use the gift. son of Laertes!
The gift!

774
00:45:02.102 --> 00:45:03.672
The gift the goddess
gave to you!

775
00:45:03.737 --> 00:45:05.406
If it can help us. use it!

776
00:45:05.472 --> 00:45:06.575
Soon. loyal Polites!

777
00:45:06.641 --> 00:45:08.209
Use it now!

778
00:45:08.275 --> 00:45:11.378
I will not let
Poseidon's pet beat us.

779
00:45:11.445 --> 00:45:17.017
He will not have the glory of
knowing I took the easy way out.

780
00:45:17.084 --> 00:45:18.385
Move!

781
00:45:18.452 --> 00:45:19.453
He is right.

782
00:45:19.521 --> 00:45:21.021
You should use it.

783
00:45:21.088 --> 00:45:24.593
It is too early in the game
for you to die. Odysseus.

784
00:45:24.659 --> 00:45:27.061
Your pride will be your ruin.

785
00:45:28.663 --> 00:45:32.833
You cannot win
this without help.

786
00:45:32.900 --> 00:45:35.769
I can beat this beast on my own.

787
00:45:35.836 --> 00:45:38.105
I do not need
your help. goddess.

788
00:45:38.172 --> 00:45:40.341
I will get home in
spite of you...

789
00:45:40.407 --> 00:45:42.009
and all the gods!

790
00:45:42.076 --> 00:45:45.112
I will waste no
more breath on you.

791
00:45:45.179 --> 00:45:48.816
Not when it can be used
for another purpose.

792
00:45:48.882 --> 00:45:50.351
My king...

793
00:45:50.417 --> 00:45:52.319
Who the hell is it
you're talking to back there?

794
00:45:52.386 --> 00:45:54.955
I will beat this beast
without your help. goddess.

795
00:46:00.427 --> 00:46:02.429
The whirlpool!

796
00:46:02.496 --> 00:46:04.532
It's coming!

797
00:46:04.599 --> 00:46:06.000
Better hold on to something.

798
00:46:08.002 --> 00:46:09.303
Hold on. men.

799
00:46:11.740 --> 00:46:13.941
It's not just any whirlpool.

800
00:46:14.008 --> 00:46:16.010
It's a creature of Poseidon.

801
00:46:16.076 --> 00:46:19.413
And if it's hungry.
we must feed it.

802
00:46:19.480 --> 00:46:23.618
We must feed it
until its belly is full.

803
00:46:23.685 --> 00:46:24.719
Until it chokes!

804
00:46:24.785 --> 00:46:26.120
Come on!

805
00:46:26.186 --> 00:46:28.389
What do you mean feed it?
Feed it with what?

806
00:46:28.455 --> 00:46:32.293
Quick!
Or we've already lost.

807
00:46:37.565 --> 00:46:40.769
Yes. what the storm
has taken from us.

808
00:46:40.834 --> 00:46:42.202
Grab the ropes.

809
00:46:42.269 --> 00:46:44.071
Anything. planks. barrels.

810
00:46:44.138 --> 00:46:46.073
Grab anything you can.

811
00:46:46.140 --> 00:46:48.309
Absolute madness.
You went mad. old man.

812
00:46:52.781 --> 00:46:55.916
Feed this beast.
Fill its belly.

813
00:46:55.983 --> 00:46:57.585
And if not...

814
00:46:57.652 --> 00:47:00.555
I will choke it myself
with my own body.

815
00:47:04.158 --> 00:47:06.628
Looks like the sea must eat.

816
00:47:06.695 --> 00:47:08.462
The fishing traps.

817
00:47:08.530 --> 00:47:10.164
Yes. the provisions. Now!

818
00:47:10.230 --> 00:47:12.567
The fishing traps?
What are we going to eat?

819
00:47:12.634 --> 00:47:14.602
We don't need them.

820
00:47:14.669 --> 00:47:16.403
We'll be home in two days.

821
00:47:16.470 --> 00:47:19.641
Or we'll be dead
trying to protect it.

822
00:47:19.708 --> 00:47:20.941
Choke on it!

823
00:47:21.008 --> 00:47:22.409
Choke on all of it!

824
00:47:25.513 --> 00:47:27.948
It's working!
It's working!

825
00:47:29.617 --> 00:47:32.286
Now what we need is distance.
Move!

826
00:47:36.990 --> 00:47:38.459
Hear me. gods!

827
00:47:38.526 --> 00:47:42.029
I am strong enough
to fight my own battles.

828
00:47:42.096 --> 00:47:44.865
Damn you! Damn you!

829
00:47:56.578 --> 00:47:58.646
Gods.

830
00:47:58.713 --> 00:48:01.048
Please. please help us.

831
00:48:02.483 --> 00:48:04.952
Father...

832
00:48:05.018 --> 00:48:07.321
Father. why have
you abandoned us?

833
00:48:12.594 --> 00:48:14.461
Odysseus is alive.

834
00:48:14.529 --> 00:48:16.698
Who... who are you?

835
00:48:16.765 --> 00:48:19.433
Save your breath. child.

836
00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:20.934
Do not fear me.

837
00:48:22.637 --> 00:48:26.073
How have you appeared like that?

838
00:48:26.140 --> 00:48:27.842
Is this some magician's trick?

839
00:48:27.908 --> 00:48:29.644
A phantasm?

840
00:48:29.711 --> 00:48:32.079
Please do not vex me. spirit!

841
00:48:32.146 --> 00:48:34.816
Athena hears your prayers.

842
00:48:34.883 --> 00:48:36.950
And you must hear my words.

843
00:48:38.553 --> 00:48:42.222
Your father has
not abandoned you.

844
00:48:42.289 --> 00:48:44.893
And neither have the gods.

845
00:48:44.958 --> 00:48:46.960
I am doing all that I can.

846
00:48:48.696 --> 00:48:51.932
Never before have I
seen a man fight for his home

847
00:48:51.999 --> 00:48:56.437
so boldly as
your father does in war.

848
00:48:56.504 --> 00:48:58.105
He honors me.

849
00:48:58.172 --> 00:49:02.309
And for that. I am
doing all that I can.

850
00:49:03.578 --> 00:49:08.516
But now. my child.
I must ask the same of you.

851
00:49:08.583 --> 00:49:11.418
You must protect
your father's house

852
00:49:11.485 --> 00:49:16.089
at all costs. from
within and from without.

853
00:49:16.156 --> 00:49:21.228
You must be prepared
to fight in war. yes.

854
00:49:21.295 --> 00:49:26.233
But you must also be careful.
watchful. and cunning.

855
00:49:28.168 --> 00:49:30.738
It is time for boys
to become men.

856
00:49:40.682 --> 00:49:42.750
I see Odysseus in you.

857
00:49:44.886 --> 00:49:46.654
Perhaps it will be enough.

858
00:49:50.692 --> 00:49:52.326
Yes.

859
00:49:52.392 --> 00:49:55.095
Perhaps it will be enough.

860
00:49:55.162 --> 00:49:58.165
Be vigilant. Telemachus.

861
00:49:58.232 --> 00:50:01.134
You will know it when
the moment comes.

862
00:50:04.137 --> 00:50:07.107
And then you
will strike...

863
00:50:07.174 --> 00:50:12.279
for your mother.
for your father. and for me.

864
00:50:16.784 --> 00:50:18.853
A toast. then.

865
00:50:18.920 --> 00:50:21.255
A toast to our health.

866
00:50:21.321 --> 00:50:27.194
and in gratitude to
my most gracious hosts.

867
00:50:27.261 --> 00:50:29.329
Who. if I might
speak freely.

868
00:50:29.396 --> 00:50:34.034
deserve a king who would
protect them at home.

869
00:50:34.101 --> 00:50:36.470
and not seek glory elsewhere.

870
00:50:38.606 --> 00:50:41.576
And I most certainly
could be that king.

871
00:50:44.278 --> 00:50:48.382
A kingdom so fine
deserves a ruler

872
00:50:48.448 --> 00:50:51.084
who would never
think to abandon it.

873
00:50:51.151 --> 00:50:53.922
This is the king's house.

874
00:50:53.988 --> 00:50:55.188
Odysseus's house.

875
00:50:55.255 --> 00:50:56.558
My father's house.

876
00:50:57.759 --> 00:50:58.826
Ah.

877
00:50:58.893 --> 00:51:03.297
And where exactly is
your father. Telemachus?

878
00:51:03.363 --> 00:51:05.098
I don't see him.

879
00:51:05.165 --> 00:51:09.102
All I see instead
is a home deserted.

880
00:51:09.169 --> 00:51:13.675
a kingdom undefended.
vulnerable.

881
00:51:13.741 --> 00:51:17.311
and of the king
himself some stories.

882
00:51:17.377 --> 00:51:20.048
The poets are talking
out on the street.

883
00:51:20.113 --> 00:51:23.851
Some say he's lost at sea.

884
00:51:23.918 --> 00:51:28.656
Others. that he dallies
with Cersei herself.

885
00:51:28.723 --> 00:51:32.660
And I myself have heard
nothing but stories of

886
00:51:32.727 --> 00:51:35.597
monsters and treasure

887
00:51:35.663 --> 00:51:38.900
and violence
and such bloodshed.

888
00:51:42.070 --> 00:51:46.507
Whatever stories you've heard.
you should know this:

889
00:51:46.574 --> 00:51:51.679
while my father is gone
and in his absence.

890
00:51:51.746 --> 00:51:56.249
I am bound to
defend what is his.

891
00:52:00.755 --> 00:52:04.124
Well. if it's a fight
you're looking for. boy.

892
00:52:04.191 --> 00:52:07.294
Honorable Antinous.

893
00:52:07.361 --> 00:52:10.665
Strong words do harm
to the digestion.

894
00:52:10.732 --> 00:52:14.669
And violence is an ill
guest in this house or any.

895
00:52:19.841 --> 00:52:22.043
Please.

896
00:52:22.110 --> 00:52:23.645
Of course. my lady.

897
00:52:25.647 --> 00:52:26.881
Of course.

898
00:52:26.948 --> 00:52:32.754
But I wouldn't need to
be a guest if my queen

899
00:52:32.820 --> 00:52:34.989
would take this suitor
to be her husband.

900
00:52:35.056 --> 00:52:37.324
I fear I cannot remarry.

901
00:52:40.695 --> 00:52:42.195
What?

902
00:52:42.262 --> 00:52:44.732
I cannot remarry
until I finish this cloak

903
00:52:44.799 --> 00:52:48.435
I've been
making for my son.

904
00:52:48.502 --> 00:52:51.471
It is only custom and proper.

905
00:52:51.539 --> 00:52:55.275
A parting gift for my
only flesh and blood.

906
00:52:57.244 --> 00:53:02.884
Before my duties as queen
to my new king

907
00:53:02.950 --> 00:53:07.187
fill my days and my hand.

908
00:53:10.058 --> 00:53:11.759
Indeed.

909
00:53:11.826 --> 00:53:15.897
Now far be it from me
to rush propriety.

910
00:53:15.963 --> 00:53:20.868
And I surely look forward
to viewing the finished product.

911
00:53:40.888 --> 00:53:46.027
Must the entire sea move
against Odysseus. Lord Poseidon?

912
00:53:46.094 --> 00:53:49.564
Behavior from such a god
seems small and petty.

913
00:53:49.630 --> 00:53:51.032
This isn't petty.

914
00:53:51.099 --> 00:53:52.867
This is revenge!

915
00:53:52.934 --> 00:53:56.704
For my son. for what
Odysseus did to my son.

916
00:53:56.771 --> 00:54:02.710
Your son. Lord Poseidon. was
harming and murdering innocents.

917
00:54:02.777 --> 00:54:06.514
Perhaps he will
think twice next time.

918
00:54:06.581 --> 00:54:09.684
Enjoy your pet hero
while you can. Athena.

919
00:54:09.751 --> 00:54:10.651
With your gifts.

920
00:54:10.718 --> 00:54:12.252
Your meddling matters not.

921
00:54:12.319 --> 00:54:15.957
Odysseus will not
leave my ocean alive.

922
00:54:26.634 --> 00:54:28.903
Polites. how is she?

923
00:54:28.970 --> 00:54:30.437
Is she patched up yet?

924
00:54:30.505 --> 00:54:32.339
She's looking pretty good.

925
00:54:32.405 --> 00:54:34.709
Pretty good.
a little bit more...

926
00:54:34.776 --> 00:54:36.409
beeswax and
she'll be good to go.

927
00:54:36.476 --> 00:54:38.646
Good. good.

928
00:54:38.713 --> 00:54:41.249
Set a course for home. Alkimos.

929
00:54:41.314 --> 00:54:42.717
Yes. my king.

930
00:54:42.784 --> 00:54:46.721
For home. and for our rewards.

931
00:54:46.788 --> 00:54:48.790
Gold.

932
00:54:48.856 --> 00:54:52.927
Yes. yes. indeed. Polites.
Indeed.

933
00:54:52.994 --> 00:54:55.395
And just on that.
by the way. I've been meaning

934
00:54:55.462 --> 00:54:56.798
to tell you. meaning
to ask about...

935
00:54:56.864 --> 00:54:57.899
Odysseus!

936
00:55:01.468 --> 00:55:02.770
A monster!

937
00:55:02.837 --> 00:55:05.072
The Scylla!
Poseidon's lap dog!

938
00:55:06.808 --> 00:55:08.009
Alkimos. no!

939
00:55:12.146 --> 00:55:13.080
Odysseus!

940
00:55:19.452 --> 00:55:22.023
What do we do?

941
00:55:22.089 --> 00:55:23.624
We try to outrun it.

942
00:55:31.165 --> 00:55:33.734
Yes... Yes. faster!

943
00:55:33.801 --> 00:55:34.902
Faster!

944
00:55:42.310 --> 00:55:43.644
No!

945
00:55:47.515 --> 00:55:50.483
No! There's not enough wind
at our back!

946
00:55:51.451 --> 00:55:54.454
Not enough wind to fight!

947
00:55:54.522 --> 00:55:56.190
Only the monster at our heels!

948
00:55:56.257 --> 00:55:57.725
Damn my pride!

949
00:56:02.530 --> 00:56:05.566
Athena! Athena!

950
00:56:06.667 --> 00:56:08.069
I'm asking for help!

951
00:56:13.507 --> 00:56:15.109
Another gift. then?

952
00:56:15.176 --> 00:56:16.978
Goddess!
We need weapons!

953
00:56:18.846 --> 00:56:21.249
Ask. and it will be yours.

954
00:56:21.315 --> 00:56:24.719
Strategy. And sight.

955
00:56:24.785 --> 00:56:25.820
Sight.

956
00:56:25.887 --> 00:56:27.588
That will be my second gift.

957
00:56:28.956 --> 00:56:30.691
To see what is
right in front of you.

958
00:56:31.626 --> 00:56:33.327
What is right in front of me?

959
00:56:33.393 --> 00:56:35.529
What? What does that mean?

960
00:56:40.001 --> 00:56:41.903
My ship.

961
00:56:41.969 --> 00:56:46.173
You ask for a weapon.
and yet you sail one.

962
00:56:46.240 --> 00:56:47.575
Yes.

963
00:56:47.642 --> 00:56:50.410
Why didn't I see that before?

964
00:56:50.477 --> 00:56:51.779
The ship is a weapon.

965
00:56:55.116 --> 00:56:57.952
Sometimes you are so
worried about what is ahead.

966
00:56:58.019 --> 00:57:01.622
that you fail to see what
is directly in front of you.

967
00:57:01.689 --> 00:57:03.224
Take heed. Odysseus.

968
00:57:03.291 --> 00:57:06.527
You will defeat the
monsters that surround you.

969
00:57:17.038 --> 00:57:18.339
Odysseus?

970
00:57:18.406 --> 00:57:20.341
Odysseus. you're steering us...

971
00:57:20.408 --> 00:57:22.009
You steer us right towards it!

972
00:57:22.076 --> 00:57:23.711
Right towards the
jaws of the beast!

973
00:57:23.778 --> 00:57:26.580
Not the jaws!
It's belly!

974
00:57:28.149 --> 00:57:30.284
We'll run it through
with the prow!

975
00:57:30.351 --> 00:57:31.919
The ship will be our sword!

976
00:57:31.986 --> 00:57:34.088
Yes! Yes!

977
00:57:42.930 --> 00:57:44.966
Odysseus. it's
not going to work!

978
00:57:45.032 --> 00:57:48.269
We've got to turn her
around or we're done for!

979
00:57:48.336 --> 00:57:50.171
The current is too strong!

980
00:57:50.237 --> 00:57:51.572
It's not working!

981
00:57:54.375 --> 00:57:56.744
She's going to eat us alive!

982
00:57:56.811 --> 00:57:58.512
Hold fast. Polites!

983
00:57:58.579 --> 00:58:01.048
We need momentum!

984
00:58:01.115 --> 00:58:02.049
I'm trying!

985
00:58:17.965 --> 00:58:20.500
That's the only
belly-full you'll get today!

986
00:58:20.568 --> 00:58:21.936
Yes. Odysseus!

987
00:58:27.308 --> 00:58:28.542
Yes!

988
00:58:34.315 --> 00:58:35.716
Come on. Telemachus.

989
00:58:35.783 --> 00:58:38.819
You must be ready to fight!

990
00:58:40.488 --> 00:58:41.622
Or we'll lose everything.

991
00:58:44.058 --> 00:58:46.794
Come home. father.
Quickly.

992
00:58:57.405 --> 00:59:00.641
The cloak you make
for me is nearly finished.

993
00:59:00.708 --> 00:59:04.445
And there are unwanted
guests in your house.

994
00:59:04.513 --> 00:59:06.347
About the cloak...

995
00:59:06.414 --> 00:59:07.715
Alas. my son.

996
00:59:07.782 --> 00:59:10.985
I fear there is still
so much work to be done.

997
00:59:11.052 --> 00:59:14.555
This cloak may take
many days to finish.

998
00:59:15.956 --> 00:59:18.025
You're undoing what you've done.

999
00:59:18.092 --> 00:59:19.193
If only I could.

1000
00:59:20.961 --> 00:59:23.197
Mother. you've
done nothing wrong.

1001
00:59:23.264 --> 00:59:24.565
It's just...

1002
00:59:24.632 --> 00:59:26.500
What?

1003
00:59:26.567 --> 00:59:28.669
Undoing the cloak every night.

1004
00:59:30.905 --> 00:59:32.706
Sometimes clever
is better than good.

1005
00:59:35.910 --> 00:59:38.446
I just pray it buys
us the time he needs.

1006
00:59:38.513 --> 00:59:41.015
And if it doesn't. then
I will be ready to fight.

1007
00:59:42.583 --> 00:59:45.052
No one is taking
this kingdom from us.

1008
00:59:46.555 --> 00:59:47.688
No one.

1009
00:59:49.023 --> 00:59:50.724
And I will be ready to fight.

1010
01:00:08.577 --> 01:00:09.710
Odysseus?

1011
01:00:11.513 --> 01:00:13.481
Odysseus.

1012
01:00:13.548 --> 01:00:15.049
Treacherous waters ahead.

1013
01:00:18.719 --> 01:00:20.988
That's treacherous
waters indeed.

1014
01:00:21.055 --> 01:00:22.957
It means we're getting
close to land now.

1015
01:00:23.023 --> 01:00:24.358
Huh.

1016
01:00:24.425 --> 01:00:27.194
That's the first good
thing I've heard all day.

1017
01:00:27.261 --> 01:00:29.029
We must stay clear
of those rocks.

1018
01:00:29.096 --> 01:00:31.198
And I have less
than a day before...

1019
01:00:31.265 --> 01:00:33.834
Before someone claims
what is rightfully yours.

1020
01:00:33.901 --> 01:00:36.605
I know. my king.
I know.

1021
01:00:36.670 --> 01:00:37.905
I am no king here.

1022
01:00:39.306 --> 01:00:40.975
There is only one
king in the ocean.

1023
01:00:41.041 --> 01:00:43.144
And I hold no favor
with him now.

1024
01:00:44.613 --> 01:00:45.779
Odysseus...

1025
01:00:45.846 --> 01:00:48.315
Can you hear that?

1026
01:00:48.382 --> 01:00:50.217
-Music?
-No.

1027
01:00:50.284 --> 01:00:51.752
No. not the songs.

1028
01:00:51.819 --> 01:00:53.087
The sirens. no.

1029
01:00:58.425 --> 01:00:59.393
No.

1030
01:00:59.460 --> 01:01:01.362
Polites. no. No!

1031
01:01:01.428 --> 01:01:02.597
Protect yourself!

1032
01:01:02.663 --> 01:01:03.731
No!

1033
01:01:03.797 --> 01:01:05.499
-Sirens.
-Not the sirens!

1034
01:01:05.567 --> 01:01:06.667
They call to me.

1035
01:01:06.734 --> 01:01:08.802
No!

1036
01:01:08.869 --> 01:01:10.605
Cover your ears!

1037
01:01:10.671 --> 01:01:12.039
Protect yourself. Polites!

1038
01:01:16.578 --> 01:01:18.647
They speak to me.

1039
01:01:18.712 --> 01:01:20.080
Cover your ears!
Protect yourself!

1040
01:01:20.147 --> 01:01:21.348
They want me to get my reward.

1041
01:01:23.552 --> 01:01:24.718
Rewards for a good man.

1042
01:01:24.785 --> 01:01:27.688
No. No!

1043
01:01:27.755 --> 01:01:29.056
They speak to me.

1044
01:01:31.759 --> 01:01:35.262
I hear the song.
It's in my head!

1045
01:01:35.329 --> 01:01:36.263
They speak to me.

1046
01:01:41.368 --> 01:01:45.439
Telemachus is the
real problem here.

1047
01:01:45.507 --> 01:01:49.376
The woman?
I can handle.

1048
01:01:49.443 --> 01:01:50.878
But the boy?

1049
01:01:52.647 --> 01:01:57.985
Any loyal dog would
struggle obeying a new master.

1050
01:01:58.052 --> 01:01:59.920
And I wouldn't blame him.

1051
01:01:59.987 --> 01:02:03.724
But once this is all mine.

1052
01:02:03.791 --> 01:02:07.194
he will still be a
thorn in my side.

1053
01:02:07.261 --> 01:02:11.131
And his mother falling
into line won't help.

1054
01:02:11.198 --> 01:02:12.900
No.

1055
01:02:12.967 --> 01:02:16.837
He's going to require
a far stronger hand.

1056
01:02:16.904 --> 01:02:18.772
It's not a matter of if.

1057
01:02:18.839 --> 01:02:22.076
Simply put. the question
becomes do I take care

1058
01:02:22.142 --> 01:02:26.480
of Telemachus now. or do
I take care of him later?

1059
01:02:30.117 --> 01:02:32.687
It's like my father used to say.

1060
01:02:32.753 --> 01:02:37.157
Only a fool leaves
today's jobs until tomorrow.

1061
01:02:37.224 --> 01:02:42.796
Well. Antinous is no fool.

1062
01:02:45.866 --> 01:02:47.801
Neither will this loyal dog.

1063
01:02:53.874 --> 01:02:55.577
No.

1064
01:02:55.644 --> 01:02:58.112
This loyal dog will be
ready for you. Antinous.

1065
01:03:06.554 --> 01:03:08.789
My reward...

1066
01:03:08.856 --> 01:03:09.990
Speak to me.

1067
01:03:11.392 --> 01:03:13.227
Odysseus!
I need to get my rewards!

1068
01:03:13.294 --> 01:03:14.995
What?
What are you doing?

1069
01:03:15.062 --> 01:03:17.398
My rewards. my gold!
They're speaking to me!

1070
01:03:17.464 --> 01:03:19.066
-Not when we're so close!
-Yes!

1071
01:03:19.133 --> 01:03:21.402
No! Just pass the rocks.
and we're nearly home!

1072
01:03:21.468 --> 01:03:22.671
They speak to me!

1073
01:03:22.737 --> 01:03:24.471
Polites!
Polites!

1074
01:03:24.539 --> 01:03:26.040
Wake up!

1075
01:03:26.106 --> 01:03:27.609
Take this beeswax!

1076
01:03:27.676 --> 01:03:28.610
Put it in your ears!

1077
01:03:28.677 --> 01:03:30.311
We must block their song!

1078
01:03:30.377 --> 01:03:33.247
We must block
the siren's song!

1079
01:03:33.314 --> 01:03:34.048
Block it!

1080
01:03:34.114 --> 01:03:36.150
We cannot hear them!

1081
01:03:36.216 --> 01:03:37.652
We've got to stay clear of them!

1082
01:03:37.719 --> 01:03:38.852
We've got to stay away!

1083
01:03:38.919 --> 01:03:40.154
Steady on the course...

1084
01:03:40.220 --> 01:03:42.590
until can't hear them!

1085
01:03:42.657 --> 01:03:43.891
Steer away...

1086
01:03:43.957 --> 01:03:45.125
Steer away.

1087
01:03:52.032 --> 01:03:54.201
That song...
That song...

1088
01:03:55.770 --> 01:03:57.137
Oh...

1089
01:03:57.204 --> 01:03:59.006
I want to hear that song.

1090
01:04:00.007 --> 01:04:01.475
Odysseus!

1091
01:04:04.945 --> 01:04:07.114
-That song...
-Odysseus!

1092
01:04:07.181 --> 01:04:09.517
Odysseus!
Don't listen to them!

1093
01:04:09.584 --> 01:04:10.752
Here!

1094
01:04:10.819 --> 01:04:12.654
No. the wax!

1095
01:04:12.721 --> 01:04:13.854
The wax!

1096
01:04:14.723 --> 01:04:16.290
The song...

1097
01:04:16.357 --> 01:04:20.160
Odysseus! We're leaving!
We're getting out of here!

1098
01:04:20.227 --> 01:04:21.995
I want to hear that song.

1099
01:04:23.832 --> 01:04:25.032
They know nothing but death!

1100
01:04:25.099 --> 01:04:26.668
-They want to help us.
-They do not.

1101
01:04:26.735 --> 01:04:29.036
-They do want to help us.
-They don't want to help us.

1102
01:04:29.103 --> 01:04:30.871
-Polites...
-Think of your family!

1103
01:04:30.938 --> 01:04:32.973
-Polites. they want to help us.
-No. no. no!

1104
01:04:33.040 --> 01:04:34.141
They will not!

1105
01:04:34.208 --> 01:04:35.510
Polites. they know
how to get home.

1106
01:04:35.577 --> 01:04:36.611
We've come this far!

1107
01:04:36.678 --> 01:04:38.178
-Polites...
-We've come this far!

1108
01:04:38.245 --> 01:04:39.480
-They only know death!
-They have wisdom!

1109
01:04:39.547 --> 01:04:40.548
They only know death!

1110
01:04:41.882 --> 01:04:42.851
Their song is wisdom.

1111
01:04:42.916 --> 01:04:44.918
Hey! Snap out of it!

1112
01:04:44.985 --> 01:04:46.153
They want to help us.

1113
01:04:46.220 --> 01:04:48.455
They know what
lies beneath the waves.

1114
01:04:48.523 --> 01:04:49.557
I must hear this song.

1115
01:04:51.058 --> 01:04:52.926
Song of the sirens.

1116
01:04:52.993 --> 01:04:55.229
What a beautiful song.

1117
01:04:55.295 --> 01:04:56.430
Huh.

1118
01:05:00.735 --> 01:05:02.369
They want to help us get home.

1119
01:05:04.572 --> 01:05:06.541
They do.

1120
01:05:06.608 --> 01:05:07.542
They have knowledge.

1121
01:05:07.609 --> 01:05:10.678
Polites. they have wisdom.

1122
01:05:11.979 --> 01:05:13.414
-Odysseus...
-Their beautiful song.

1123
01:05:13.480 --> 01:05:14.549
I must hear it.

1124
01:05:14.616 --> 01:05:17.084
Odysseus. they know
nothing but death.

1125
01:05:19.086 --> 01:05:20.354
They have knowledge.

1126
01:05:20.421 --> 01:05:22.089
They know nothing but death.

1127
01:05:22.156 --> 01:05:23.457
Think of home.

1128
01:05:26.460 --> 01:05:28.128
The song.

1129
01:05:28.195 --> 01:05:30.765
No. Polites. we
must steer towards them.

1130
01:05:30.832 --> 01:05:31.800
Polites. they want to help us!

1131
01:05:31.866 --> 01:05:33.033
No. they don't!

1132
01:05:33.100 --> 01:05:35.537
Yes!
Their song!

1133
01:05:38.305 --> 01:05:39.574
I want to hear their song...

1134
01:05:46.180 --> 01:05:49.383
Please. Polites.
They sing for me!

1135
01:05:49.450 --> 01:05:50.785
Odysseus!

1136
01:05:50.852 --> 01:05:53.253
Odysseus!
Hear me. Odysseus!

1137
01:05:55.155 --> 01:05:58.760
You must not listen
to them. Odysseus!

1138
01:05:58.827 --> 01:06:00.494
I can only hear their song.

1139
01:06:00.562 --> 01:06:01.896
Odysseus!

1140
01:06:01.962 --> 01:06:03.464
No!

1141
01:06:03.531 --> 01:06:05.332
You can't hear me
over their song!

1142
01:06:06.400 --> 01:06:07.735
Odysseus!

1143
01:06:07.802 --> 01:06:11.104
You will die if you don't
make it past these rocks!

1144
01:06:11.171 --> 01:06:15.976
And if you cannot hear me.
I cannot help you!

1145
01:06:16.043 --> 01:06:17.579
I cannot help you.

1146
01:06:19.848 --> 01:06:21.081
Odysseus!

1147
01:06:21.148 --> 01:06:22.617
Odysseus. no!

1148
01:06:26.353 --> 01:06:29.389
Polites. we must
steer away from the rocks.

1149
01:06:29.456 --> 01:06:31.258
Please steer away from them.

1150
01:06:35.362 --> 01:06:37.231
We must get to Ithaca.

1151
01:06:37.297 --> 01:06:38.800
They will give us
a hero's welcome.

1152
01:06:38.867 --> 01:06:40.467
A king's welcome.

1153
01:06:44.171 --> 01:06:45.907
Damn the sirens.

1154
01:06:45.974 --> 01:06:48.275
And damn these seas. too.

1155
01:06:48.342 --> 01:06:50.512
Polites. please forgive me.

1156
01:06:50.578 --> 01:06:53.715
You have saved
both of our lives.

1157
01:06:53.781 --> 01:06:55.984
It was an honor. my king.

1158
01:06:56.049 --> 01:06:58.252
But now our course is set.

1159
01:06:58.318 --> 01:07:00.187
You are almost home.

1160
01:07:00.254 --> 01:07:02.122
And that is your reward.

1161
01:07:03.390 --> 01:07:07.494
But mind. my king.
my reward is treasure.

1162
01:07:07.562 --> 01:07:10.030
You must listen to me.
You don't understand.

1163
01:07:10.097 --> 01:07:12.299
No. no. no. I do understand.

1164
01:07:12.366 --> 01:07:14.636
You have a gift from the gods.

1165
01:07:14.702 --> 01:07:16.403
And Ithaca. now
that is your reward.

1166
01:07:16.470 --> 01:07:17.705
Now I am in pursuit of mine.

1167
01:07:17.772 --> 01:07:20.207
You said. your words.

1168
01:07:20.274 --> 01:07:21.643
What do you mean?

1169
01:07:21.709 --> 01:07:23.410
Gifts for good men.
Did you not?

1170
01:07:23.477 --> 01:07:25.078
Please. you do not understand.

1171
01:07:25.145 --> 01:07:28.382
No. I do understand. It's you
that doesn't understand.

1172
01:07:28.448 --> 01:07:30.652
I saw Athena
herself give it to you.

1173
01:07:30.718 --> 01:07:32.286
-I saw her.
-No. no.

1174
01:07:32.352 --> 01:07:33.821
A gift from the gods. Reward.

1175
01:07:33.888 --> 01:07:35.222
No. it's not a gift.

1176
01:07:35.289 --> 01:07:37.124
-Oh. it's not a gift?
-No. it's not.

1177
01:07:37.190 --> 01:07:38.392
I see it.

1178
01:07:38.458 --> 01:07:40.795
I see. clever Polites.
loyal Polites.

1179
01:07:40.862 --> 01:07:42.296
worthy of scars Polites.

1180
01:07:42.362 --> 01:07:45.265
but not worthy of a gift
from the gods. is that it?

1181
01:07:45.332 --> 01:07:47.702
Please listen to me.
Please listen to me.

1182
01:07:47.769 --> 01:07:49.303
Exactly like Troy. is it?

1183
01:07:49.369 --> 01:07:51.606
Exactly like Troy.

1184
01:07:51.673 --> 01:07:53.140
I am going to take
what is owed to me.

1185
01:07:53.206 --> 01:07:54.542
For good men.

1186
01:07:54.609 --> 01:07:58.345
No. no. do not take that.
Do not take that!

1187
01:07:58.412 --> 01:08:00.113
Bring it back.
You do not understand.

1188
01:08:00.180 --> 01:08:02.016
-No. stop.
-I do understand.

1189
01:08:02.082 --> 01:08:04.451
Stop!
Polites. please. please.

1190
01:08:04.519 --> 01:08:08.188
My King. I am only opening this

1191
01:08:08.255 --> 01:08:09.591
because this is
what is owed to me.

1192
01:08:09.657 --> 01:08:11.091
-No.
-Yes.

1193
01:08:22.469 --> 01:08:23.605
Athena.

1194
01:08:25.039 --> 01:08:26.574
Athena. please.

1195
01:08:26.641 --> 01:08:29.010
Athena will not
save you. Odysseus.

1196
01:08:29.077 --> 01:08:31.378
We will finish this war
you started.

1197
01:08:31.445 --> 01:08:35.115
And it will end with your blood
filling my oceans.

1198
01:08:56.804 --> 01:09:00.908
Perhaps the fates are more
generous than we thought.

1199
01:09:00.975 --> 01:09:02.376
Athena.

1200
01:09:02.442 --> 01:09:05.145
Even the winds had mercy
on you and brought you home.

1201
01:09:07.214 --> 01:09:09.182
Reward. Reward.

1202
01:09:11.919 --> 01:09:17.424
Great Odysseus finally returned
to the shores of Ithaca.

1203
01:09:18.693 --> 01:09:19.927
Ithaca.

1204
01:09:19.994 --> 01:09:24.164
Telemachus...
Penelope!

1205
01:09:24.231 --> 01:09:27.135
The great Odysseus...

1206
01:09:27.200 --> 01:09:29.604
At the end of his ropes.

1207
01:09:31.739 --> 01:09:33.407
No.

1208
01:09:33.473 --> 01:09:34.776
Not yet.
Not quite.

1209
01:09:36.276 --> 01:09:38.311
Look.

1210
01:09:38.378 --> 01:09:39.847
There. Your Majesty.

1211
01:09:46.054 --> 01:09:48.723
Your people are in panic.

1212
01:09:48.790 --> 01:09:51.626
Perhaps there is no more
glory left for you here.

1213
01:09:53.861 --> 01:09:57.632
Penelope and Telemachus
are doing all they can.

1214
01:09:57.699 --> 01:10:00.835
But your city is
being taken by force.

1215
01:10:00.902 --> 01:10:03.270
My world burns.

1216
01:10:03.336 --> 01:10:06.741
And the gods abandon me
with my hands tied.

1217
01:10:06.808 --> 01:10:09.342
I can offer no more aid.
and you know this.

1218
01:10:13.413 --> 01:10:16.216
By breathing wind
into your sails.

1219
01:10:16.283 --> 01:10:19.687
strategizing your
boat as a weapon.

1220
01:10:19.754 --> 01:10:22.422
and giving you a bag of wind.

1221
01:10:22.489 --> 01:10:26.561
your three gifts have been used.

1222
01:10:26.627 --> 01:10:30.363
But great goddess.
I never opened the bag of winds.

1223
01:10:30.430 --> 01:10:34.035
It was Polites.
Polites opened the bag of winds.

1224
01:10:34.102 --> 01:10:35.937
Not I.

1225
01:10:36.003 --> 01:10:37.404
A wrinkle.

1226
01:10:38.940 --> 01:10:43.310
Perhaps it is enough
for the gods to allow me

1227
01:10:43.376 --> 01:10:47.515
to aid you one last
time on your journey.

1228
01:10:47.582 --> 01:10:51.251
I have one boon.
One gift left.

1229
01:10:51.318 --> 01:10:53.521
I just pray I don't
have to use it.

1230
01:10:53.588 --> 01:10:57.859
Yes. but you cannot
just go home. Odysseus.

1231
01:10:57.925 --> 01:11:00.393
Not anymore.

1232
01:11:00.460 --> 01:11:03.765
The people of Ithaca.
they are a mob.

1233
01:11:03.831 --> 01:11:06.500
They run through the
streets hungry for blood.

1234
01:11:06.567 --> 01:11:08.536
They would have yours.

1235
01:11:08.603 --> 01:11:10.705
You will not make it past them.

1236
01:11:10.772 --> 01:11:13.608
You will not even make it
to your front door.

1237
01:11:13.674 --> 01:11:17.979
And if you did. the suitors
would be waiting for you.

1238
01:11:19.947 --> 01:11:21.983
In disguise.

1239
01:11:22.049 --> 01:11:24.585
In disguise to hide
my face in my own kingdom.

1240
01:11:24.652 --> 01:11:26.453
I shall dress as a
wandering beggar

1241
01:11:26.521 --> 01:11:28.156
and learn how things stand.

1242
01:11:28.222 --> 01:11:31.192
What will you do.
Great Odysseus?

1243
01:11:31.259 --> 01:11:32.794
I will defend my home.

1244
01:11:32.860 --> 01:11:34.028
My family.

1245
01:11:34.095 --> 01:11:36.429
I must stop this
before it's too late.

1246
01:11:36.496 --> 01:11:38.431
Or even if it's as you say.

1247
01:11:38.498 --> 01:11:41.803
there's no glory
left for either of us.

1248
01:11:43.470 --> 01:11:46.007
Finish the game. Odysseus.

1249
01:11:46.073 --> 01:11:47.909
And finish it well.

1250
01:11:47.975 --> 01:11:52.280
For not all gods
have abandoned you.

1251
01:11:52.345 --> 01:11:54.982
And Poseidon still
thirsts for revenge.

1252
01:12:04.258 --> 01:12:06.326
We must do something. Mother.

1253
01:12:06.393 --> 01:12:08.062
No.

1254
01:12:08.129 --> 01:12:09.396
I will not let them kill you.

1255
01:12:09.462 --> 01:12:10.998
You must get
control of the city.

1256
01:12:11.065 --> 01:12:14.902
We will wait until
your father returns.

1257
01:12:14.969 --> 01:12:16.204
Rioting!

1258
01:12:16.270 --> 01:12:17.972
Looting and violence.

1259
01:12:18.039 --> 01:12:21.042
and you want to wait for
Odysseus to return?

1260
01:12:22.810 --> 01:12:25.378
Do you still think
you'll have a kingdom by then?

1261
01:12:29.416 --> 01:12:33.120
Without a king.
my queen.

1262
01:12:33.187 --> 01:12:38.458
the city succumbs to
its more primal urges.

1263
01:12:38.526 --> 01:12:42.063
I will take your hand
and the crown with it.

1264
01:12:42.129 --> 01:12:47.400
And all will be well
when King Antinous reigns.

1265
01:12:48.501 --> 01:12:50.805
It is time. my lord.

1266
01:12:50.872 --> 01:12:54.374
Time enough indeed
for the final challenge.

1267
01:12:57.410 --> 01:13:01.082
No more games. loyal widow.

1268
01:13:01.148 --> 01:13:03.383
Being king is no game.

1269
01:13:03.450 --> 01:13:04.785
And only the worthy
wear our crown

1270
01:13:04.852 --> 01:13:06.821
and complete this final task.

1271
01:13:09.156 --> 01:13:13.460
Only our king can fire an
arrow through those axe blades.

1272
01:13:13.527 --> 01:13:16.496
And only our king has done it.

1273
01:13:16.564 --> 01:13:20.701
So are you our king. Antinous?

1274
01:13:20.768 --> 01:13:26.473
Or does Odysseus. even in
his absence. carry the crown?

1275
01:13:26.540 --> 01:13:29.110
You're not worth of such
a great feat!

1276
01:13:29.176 --> 01:13:31.012
I challenge you for
my Father's kingdom!

1277
01:13:31.078 --> 01:13:32.713
Snake in the grass!

1278
01:13:35.082 --> 01:13:36.918
Stay in your place. pup!

1279
01:13:36.984 --> 01:13:38.753
Telemachus!

1280
01:13:38.819 --> 01:13:43.024
But if I must. I will
teach you to keep your place!

1281
01:13:44.558 --> 01:13:47.094
The crown will never be yours!

1282
01:13:49.462 --> 01:13:51.098
Snake in the grass!

1283
01:13:57.505 --> 01:14:00.041
Interloper! Villain!

1284
01:14:00.107 --> 01:14:01.776
Yes. I am.

1285
01:14:03.177 --> 01:14:06.047
And much worse.

1286
01:14:06.113 --> 01:14:07.648
Begging your apologies.

1287
01:14:07.715 --> 01:14:11.052
I was merely returning
the young man his sword.

1288
01:14:14.454 --> 01:14:16.190
I...

1289
01:14:16.257 --> 01:14:20.161
I would like to ask the young
lady if I may compete.

1290
01:14:20.227 --> 01:14:21.228
Another suitor?

1291
01:14:24.131 --> 01:14:26.033
With the queen's
permission. of course.

1292
01:14:32.306 --> 01:14:34.275
We need no more suitors!

1293
01:14:34.342 --> 01:14:35.543
I will--

1294
01:14:35.609 --> 01:14:36.811
The courtesy of
my husband's house

1295
01:14:36.877 --> 01:14:38.646
is much diminished
as of late.

1296
01:14:42.450 --> 01:14:44.185
You may compete.

1297
01:14:44.251 --> 01:14:47.254
And I pray you might
restore what has been lost.

1298
01:14:47.321 --> 01:14:51.592
Only Odysseus can put an
arrow through those axe blades.

1299
01:14:51.659 --> 01:14:55.963
So. let's see how good you are.

1300
01:14:56.030 --> 01:14:56.964
Good.

1301
01:14:59.467 --> 01:15:01.902
Clever.

1302
01:15:01.969 --> 01:15:03.671
Clever is better than good.

1303
01:15:15.182 --> 01:15:17.018
It's a farce!

1304
01:15:17.084 --> 01:15:20.054
He can't even keep the
arrow straight. my queen.

1305
01:15:21.322 --> 01:15:24.792
Best keep your eye
on the target. old man.

1306
01:15:26.460 --> 01:15:30.231
So. only Odysseus
himself can make this shot.

1307
01:15:48.149 --> 01:15:50.551
And I must be Odysseus.

1308
01:15:50.618 --> 01:15:52.720
But Odysseus is dead!

1309
01:15:52.787 --> 01:15:55.022
-No!
-Father!

1310
01:15:57.258 --> 01:16:01.328
You have overstayed your
welcome in my house too long!

1311
01:16:01.395 --> 01:16:02.663
Antinous!

1312
01:16:04.465 --> 01:16:06.300
You can leave on
your own accord.

1313
01:16:06.367 --> 01:16:07.701
Never!

1314
01:16:07.768 --> 01:16:10.738
This kingdom is mine!

1315
01:16:10.805 --> 01:16:12.840
Or you can go another way!

1316
01:16:19.413 --> 01:16:23.417
Death is too good for you.

1317
01:16:23.484 --> 01:16:24.819
Watch your tongue!

1318
01:16:24.885 --> 01:16:27.588
Or we will take it from you.

1319
01:16:27.655 --> 01:16:29.023
No!

1320
01:16:35.930 --> 01:16:37.064
My gods!

1321
01:16:38.599 --> 01:16:39.767
Help me!

1322
01:16:39.834 --> 01:16:41.969
Have mercy on me!

1323
01:16:58.319 --> 01:16:59.820
Here I am. monster!

1324
01:17:04.391 --> 01:17:07.328
I'll take everything
from you. Odysseus!

1325
01:17:07.394 --> 01:17:08.696
I will drown all of Ithaca.

1326
01:17:08.762 --> 01:17:11.365
drown your house.
and your family!

1327
01:17:11.432 --> 01:17:12.700
No! No!

1328
01:17:12.766 --> 01:17:14.435
Here I am! Here I am!

1329
01:17:14.502 --> 01:17:16.203
I'm the one you want!

1330
01:17:16.270 --> 01:17:18.239
Take me! Take me!

1331
01:17:20.007 --> 01:17:21.075
Father!

1332
01:17:22.511 --> 01:17:23.744
Father!

1333
01:17:46.200 --> 01:17:47.201
Odysseus?

1334
01:17:48.802 --> 01:17:49.937
Odysseus!

1335
01:17:51.438 --> 01:17:52.740
No!

1336
01:17:52.806 --> 01:17:54.842
What did he say to you. son?

1337
01:17:54.909 --> 01:17:56.677
Tell me!
Tell me quickly!

1338
01:17:56.744 --> 01:17:58.345
What were his
final words to you?

1339
01:17:58.412 --> 01:18:00.147
I don't understand!

1340
01:18:01.482 --> 01:18:02.416
Telemachus...

1341
01:18:02.483 --> 01:18:05.452
What were his final words?

1342
01:18:05.520 --> 01:18:08.889
He said. third gift.

1343
01:18:10.291 --> 01:18:11.225
Third gift?

1344
01:18:13.260 --> 01:18:14.195
And then...

1345
01:18:15.530 --> 01:18:16.864
And then nothing more.

1346
01:18:21.869 --> 01:18:23.237
So clever.

1347
01:18:24.539 --> 01:18:26.473
The king of Ithaca.

1348
01:18:26.541 --> 01:18:28.342
Clever to his last.

1349
01:18:29.944 --> 01:18:31.111
Oh. goddess Athena.

1350
01:18:32.647 --> 01:18:34.014
My love.

1351
01:18:34.081 --> 01:18:38.852
You have suffered
enough these past many days.

1352
01:18:38.919 --> 01:18:41.422
But the game's over.

1353
01:18:41.488 --> 01:18:43.757
Odysseus...

1354
01:18:43.824 --> 01:18:44.959
Wins.

1355
01:18:45.025 --> 01:18:46.860
What do you mean?

1356
01:18:46.927 --> 01:18:48.329
He didn't win.

1357
01:18:48.395 --> 01:18:50.164
He's dead.
He's gone!

1358
01:18:50.231 --> 01:18:54.034
Do not be troubled.
son of Odysseus.

1359
01:18:54.101 --> 01:18:58.038
Once again. your
father's glory honors me.

1360
01:18:59.940 --> 01:19:02.209
With his final breath.

1361
01:19:02.276 --> 01:19:06.180
your husband requested his
last wish.

1362
01:19:08.882 --> 01:19:10.784
May I grant it?

1363
01:19:10.851 --> 01:19:11.986
Yes.

1364
01:19:15.322 --> 01:19:16.257
Yes. please.

1365
01:19:19.426 --> 01:19:23.364
Clever is indeed
greater than good.

1366
01:19:37.746 --> 01:19:39.446
-Father!
-He's alive!

1367
01:19:41.750 --> 01:19:43.317
Goddess Athena. thank you.

1368
01:19:43.384 --> 01:19:46.186
It was your husband
who outsmarted death.

1369
01:19:47.855 --> 01:19:50.891
I am glad to see
you all reunited.

1370
01:19:59.701 --> 01:20:01.536
My son...

1371
01:20:01.603 --> 01:20:02.537
Oh. my son.

1372
01:20:04.773 --> 01:20:05.906
I was gone.

1373
01:20:07.341 --> 01:20:08.309
The goddess.

1374
01:20:11.145 --> 01:20:15.517
Athena has granted me
my third wish.

1375
01:20:17.284 --> 01:20:20.354
My father more clever
than the gods themselves.

1376
01:20:27.729 --> 01:20:30.297
The river Styx can wait...

1377
01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:35.035
But a moment longer.

1378
01:20:35.936 --> 01:20:37.071
Oh...

1379
01:20:38.573 --> 01:20:40.040
You took your time. old man.

1380
01:20:41.710 --> 01:20:43.377
The wind.

1381
01:20:43.444 --> 01:20:44.546
The wind was against me.

1382
01:20:46.748 --> 01:20:50.117
I have heard such stories.

1383
01:20:53.722 --> 01:20:56.825
You seem as if from a dream.

1384
01:20:56.890 --> 01:20:58.827
Are you really here?

1385
01:20:58.892 --> 01:21:01.862
Or are the gods
still playing games.

1386
01:21:04.098 --> 01:21:09.637
I have not the strength
for their sport any longer.

1387
01:21:09.704 --> 01:21:10.839
Nor do I.

1388
01:21:10.904 --> 01:21:12.473
Nor do I. my queen.

1389
01:21:15.543 --> 01:21:19.413
King of Ithaca. why have
you returned to this place?

1390
01:21:25.152 --> 01:21:28.790
I have but one goal.

1391
01:21:28.857 --> 01:21:29.990
One destination.

1392
01:21:33.127 --> 01:21:37.297
Not Ithaca. not this house.

1393
01:21:37.364 --> 01:21:39.333
not the crown was my goal.

1394
01:21:42.537 --> 01:21:46.206
I care not for the seas
or the skies.

1395
01:21:48.142 --> 01:21:51.613
I sought no monsters. nor gods.

1396
01:21:54.549 --> 01:21:56.216
I only sought you.

1397
01:21:58.553 --> 01:21:59.621
Only you.

1398
01:21:59.687 --> 01:22:05.192
You... You were the
safe harbor I fought

1399
01:22:05.259 --> 01:22:09.029
so desperately to get home to.

1400
01:22:17.971 --> 01:22:19.973
And home you will stay.

1401
01:22:21.108 --> 01:22:22.242
Yes. I will.

1402
01:22:26.648 --> 01:22:27.615
Home.

1403
01:22:29.918 --> 01:22:32.252
The only journey
worth the fight.

1404
01:22:38.760 --> 01:22:40.595
Home.

1405
01:22:40.662 --> 01:22:42.162
Home at last.

1405
01:22:43.305 --> 01:23:43.440
Do you want subtitles for any video?
